I've had  for both Soc 2310 and 3315. His class format is pretty easy to follow: A lecture mixed with an article or two per week, a discussion board and a four question quiz. There is a mid-term and final which are mostly multiple choice with a few short answer, as well as a final 4-6 page paper. It's clear he cares about his students!

I think he genuinely wants his students to learn the material, but his lectures were confusing. Even though he is a non-native speaker, I feel like the language barrier was not the issue. He just had a really hard time teaching the material due to being very disorganized. We wrote lots of papers, and I don't think he really graded any of them.
The best class have taken.

There were multiple times I reached out to Prof  and (if) I got a reply, I legit said aloud, "well thanks for nothing." I cannot express how impersonal this class was. I understand it was asynchronous but I literally felt like I was 100% teaching myself. It was so hard to keep up with the lengthy readings and long lectures. Do not recommend.

Chip is really kind, but he cares more about content then students. There is a quiz before every class and the Assignments take forever. If you are just taking this class to get an easy A, its not. you will work for it. The class was very thought provoking though.
Hes a little all over the place but overall he was inspiring and a cool professor. East class
If you are a bad test taker, this class can be challenging, since only 3 midterms will make up your grade.. no homework, quizzes etc. Prof. Lount loves his job and it shows in lecture

He's very ambiguous. Gives you a group paper and group assignments with no real directions. Luckily, they're not that hard and you can kind of do your own thing. Every week we had an in class assignment (writing your opinion) that was for a participation grade. His lectures don't make sense. MCQ on tests are easy, but the short answer are hard.
IMO the online lectures are very hard to follow because he rambles a lot. Not very interesting either and very time consuming course.

The class was fine. It was not particularly interesting to me. I got a low grade because I put very little effort in but it was definitely not a hard class. There was also a lot of extra credit offered. It was not a bad class I just don't like statistics and I wasn't engaged in it .

Very very intelligent. Has written several books on this topic. Knows a ton. Need to attend class to have much of an idea of what's going on. Lectures are pretty good, but sometimes can get boring and he likes to go off on tangents occassionally. Not easy, but not difficult either if you pay attention. I got a B on the final and didn't read.

Mr.  is a great teacher don't get me wrong but he is extremely difficult at grading and he doesn't cut you a break. The final exam questions are very tough to understand. He is a great teacher but I don't recommend him due to his extremely difficult grading style. Take someone else who is easier if you can.

I definitely not recommend taking this class with her. She is super nice, but nice well experienced with the material. She reads from slides most of the time and her exam questions are not related to what she gave in the lecture.
She's so nice and very helpful. Just pay attention and you'll do fine.
Exams were tough. Paper has no clear grading criteria so its hard to know whats expected for a sizable chunk if your grade. Interesting guy, interesting topics, but be cautious with this class.

Juggernaut of information to absorb, even with the online Study Guides. Brilliant man. Go to every class, sit in front, record his lecture, and listen to them while munching on some chips. And go to the operas and orchestras for 6% extra credit.

This is a must to take psych class!! Dr.  makes an hour and 48 min seem like half an hour. His lectures are outstanding, applicable to real world, nothing obscure. But careful!His tests have a lot of stats and are long. Even so, its a well balanced class and very informative and entertaining. Overall is great, study and you can easily get an A.

Very nice and entertaining in class but sometimes disorganized and not very concise at all!! Overall good intentions, but would get on rampages about irrelevant topics. Would not take this class if I could do it all over again.

This professor was very enthusiastic, she was willing to help and very easy to talk to. She doesn't make it mandatory to come to class but if you do majority of what's on the exams is talked about. The first exam was very easy but the final was kind basically to get the slackers.....

is a great professor and I would take every class taught by him if I could. He is very understanding and is willing to help with anything. I missed a few points on a quiz one time and emailed him to ask for an explanation. He gave me 2 points back because I am a good student and he hates to see me lose points. Great guy!
I enjoyed taking his class. You should go to class and study for exams. Take advantage of extra credit. Overall pretty easy class
Literally never went to class and only watched the review lectures. Super easy class and super smart guy
I love Dr. , awesome class, have to take it if you are a psych major, he is my honors advisor, and I could not have asked for better..!!!!!!! :)

You need the book for the online exams. I can't imagine trying to do those without it. Participation matters a lot, it's like 30% of your grade, but she's hilarious so it was rare that I didn't want to go to class.

He's passionate and lecture isn't bad, but he goes off on tangents sometimes. Slides are poor and bare minimum. Midterm and final were cake, but the quizzes are a bit difficult and worth 100 points! A paper of five pages is only worth 10 points, though....?

Great, easy class for undergrads. Lots of notes and quizzes, but easy. Keep in mind old quiz questions when taking final exam. Discussion boards, movie tests, and final paper very graded on participation. No textbook. Worst part was he turned off the final grade on carmen so you don't know your grade or "what-if"

If you aren't considering law school, or you don't have an interest in the Supreme Court, DO NOT TAKE THIS COURSE. That said,  is brilliant and highly regarded, look at his CV. I really liked this class. It was low-effort but topical/useful/informative. There are textbook quizzes on Carmen, but they aren't worth much and the exams were based entirely on lecture. Lecture kind of drones on, but he posts the slides online and the exams were cake.

took on the task of teaching this new course, and I think she did an excellent job of doing so. 
 Dr.  was very communicative in what exactly we had to do, and always greeted us with kindness and a smile. She always encouraged us to ask questions about the material, and she did a great job of explaining everything. Just loved her.

I have this prof in 2 classes, he is not very approachable. In both classes, he runs out of class room as soon as it's over. He says see him after class but you can't, he is gone within a few min of it ending. Notes are confusing, not very organized. Wish he would give us full notes and just made us participate more. Seems like a good guy otherwise
I like the guy but the test are tough.

was great! Very accessible and funny. You don't need a textbook and honestly don't need to go to class unless it's a review day. Tests determine grade, but they aren't impossible. Studying review slides and not going to class will get you an A- or A

The material is interesting. However, he did not test over what he taught in class. He also did not test over the book. He admitted at the end of the quarter that he didn't even write his own tests. The grades were so bad he wouldn't even post the averages.

The slides are disorganized and hard to read his handwriting. I took the first in person class after Covid and he probably had too high expectation on students. The exams are heavy with two midterms and one final, each with hard prove with few numbers and given little partial credits. He has few examples on slides. Consider not taking his class.
Nothing spectacular by any means. She is an okay professor but is somewhat uniformed about current events, which is surprising for a sociology instructor.

is a great teacher that cares a lot about her students. She expects a lot out you, but it never seemed like an unreasonable amount of work. It may seem like there are a lot of assignments at first, but they are all pretty easy if you give yourself time and don't wait until the last minute to start. Tests aren't a cakewalk, but not too hard.

Psychology is my major and this class made me question whether or not I wanted to do it. He made the tests way too difficult and gave us a curve because most of the class did poorly. The only reason I passed was because of the good curve!

Pretty good teacher. The class itself is pretty boring but it isn't difficult. Going to class def makes it a lot easier. He gives an opportunity for extra credit that can really help your grade if you do it.

He is very laid back and does not make the class a heavy burden. If you go to class you should do well. Class can get boring often, which is why people skip. Textbook readings are unnecessary but outside readings appear on tests. Three exams (non-cumulative) and a paper. Exams are MC and short answer and mostly straightforward right off his slides

This class is not an easy A for a gen ed. He is a harsh grader, but only because he wants you to learn. Content is interesting, but there is a ton of outside work. Go to class because there are pop quizzes that are 20% if your grade on the homework readings. You have to try hard in this class to do well and one grade can offset your entire grade
Super easy class and Dr.  shows that she cares about her students

Lectures were bland, but posted online. Class was relatively easy, as I never read the book and only studied a loose hour before the exams, earning a B overall. Then again, I'd also taken a couple overlapping Psych courses. I think my boredom with the material contributed to my lack of motivation tbh. Average course overall. DOES DROP 1 EXAM GRADE!

Material is interesting, but there's a lot of it. Professor  makes pretty confusing Powerpoint slides that don't help much, and will sometimes breeze through confusing concepts without clarifying or connecting them to broader ideas. Read the text before lecture to get the most out of his class.

I'm not a psych major, and I didn't really think there would be a lot to learn about in this class since the topic is so narrow. Man was I wrong! Dr.  knows his stuff and makes it very easy to learn all of the material. His tests are tough, but not impossible. There are TONS of theories to learn and lots of reading to do in order to pass.

Just had to comment upon the comments: I had   for 2 classes in the 1970's, and he was absolutely fabulous then, and by far the best teacher in the department. I'm so gratified to see he has aged like a fine wine.

is so lovely and approachable. The class wasn't difficult, but there's lots of lectures to keep up with which can be tedious. If you slack off and don't watch them when posted, it will be tedious and a pain watching them all to catch up. Take good notes on everything since quiz/exam questions are picky. Just be organized and you'll be fine.

His lectures are okay. There can be really interesting content, but sometimes he just goes on unrelated rants. He says he's a realist every time he gets a chance and says some really out of pocket stuff sometimes but in a funny way. Class is super easy though, I would take it if you need a GPA boost.

I took the honors version. Great class and super easy. Only need the reader, don't waste time purchasing textbook. Midterm and final are essays that you get to make outlines for and use on the test. Kinda boring but easy GEC.
Half of these reviews sound like they were written by the professor and do not match the reality of her teaching style/class experience. She also gets unfavorable reviews taken down so beware.

Proff  is best described as a "total bro". He explains everything so clearly and has met and worked with half the people they teach about in the book. Very understanding. I bombed one exam and did amazing on the other two so he just dropped the bad one because I asked him nicely and participated in class. I would absolutely recommend.

I feel like he is unfairly criticized. Yes, he can come off as demeaning as times but his lectures are extremely informative and I learned a lot. You can tell he is very passionate about what he teaches and if you take good notes and study you should be fine. Note that there is a lot of reading every week.

He knows a lot and will help you if you ever need anything. Lectures are not too fast, has powerpoints online, grading is straight forward, you will want to take him again. (keep an eye out for his jokes, subtle at times but hilarious if you get it) plus he's tall and kinda cuute..

Really good professor. His teaching style goes a little off the average OSU professor, which is why it upsets people. Lectures are enjoyable, and the material is heavy just like his grading for exams, but it is not that deep. Genuinely a funny and enjoyable professor and his accent has nothing to do with it. Recommend the class a 100%

I took 551 with this guy and it was hard but i still did well and liked it. Now 555 is way hard. The text book is just a regular book. and he makes it sound like he'll pull obvious things from it but there were questions on things i didn't even remember reading. I'm not saying don't take the class cause it is interesting. But be ready to study.

I didnt attend this class very much after the first exam.She gives us the powerpoints online between that and the book I didnt need the class.She basically just goes over the powerpoints anyway.I attended maybe five or six classes and still got an A.But I did study alot my main issue is she doesn't tell you what you miss on quizzes,just the grade.
Good guy, wants you to learn in fun ways. Doesnt just push tests or massive papers.

I love him *so* much! Ben is so nice and funny and helpful. I had a blast in his class and he is so smart. Yeah, you might not get As on all the papers, but there are more than enough points to make up for it. Lots of extra credit too, makes up for the pop quizzes (drops the worst ones). Honestly such a cool dude. Love him, wish it was my major.
His lectures can be a little dry, but the class is super easy to get an A in.
A little unorganized at times, but overall not a bad professor. If anything, the TA's will prevent you from understanding the material by making things more confusing than necessary.

Joe is a decent professor. His lectures aren't super helpful because he goes into too much theory. However, he does try to "dumb down" differential equations for the class, which helps a lot. His exams are fair, with some being pretty easy and others being pretty challenging. Overall, he is a good professor and you should do fine in the class

Go to class because all the notes are taken in class. You don't need a textbook or anything but remember there is no curve. I was .01 away from an A and could not be rounded but overall she is a super nice professor and it should be easy as long as you study.

Class isnt really interesting and is just way harder than it needs to be, second lowest gpa on the department and spends the whole lecture on one topic going in more depth than he needs to be, attendance is t mandatory but if you dont go there are 0 resources to have a majority of the material explained to you

He doesn't give students feedback on exams and his rubric is based on what he thinks was important for the readings. Almost impossible to improve in this class. He talks about his favorite things about the class at the end of the semester and mentions some students by name and not others.
Dr.  is fantastic, but a little boring to listen to at 8 a.m. He is an expert in the field of attitudes and persuasion, and it's easy to learn from him.

This is the second course I have taken with Dr. , the first being SOC3306. Many are rating him quite unfairly. I took this class in AU20 but i noticed all the negative reviews and thoroughly disagree. Professor  seems like an extremely nice guy. I just think the way he teaches isnt effective at all. He is good lecturer but the class is VERY EXHAUSTING. you'll have to read over 300 SLIDES PER MIDTERM(this is no exaggeration). Dr.  is a nice guy but I wasn't particularly found of his module. I thought that the oil spillHiroshima& Nagasaki stuff was interesting but the rest was really dry because it was mostly bio stats. Easy class...lots of work for a 110 course, though. Dr.  is pretty funny and has entertaining lectures, she also enjoys pop quizzes. A ton of reading and 5 mandatory papers. Good class, so long as you have an interest in womens studies

You don't need the book but you must go to lecture, the online homework is pretty hard but the exams are easy, you get to take a cheat sheet with you to the exams. he is very considerate for students. I would definitely take his class again

She was so sweet! She seemed to genuinely care about her students and had interesting activities to do in break-out rooms (which I usually hate). Her tests are moderately difficult but all content is from her lectures which is nice since you don't have to guess what material is from the book/lecture. I definitely recommend !!

Dr.  is one of the best lecturers I've had at OSU. It's obvious he knows a lot about sociology and criminology, but he isn't arrogant about it. He genuinely is interested in teaching his students, and he also gives pointers for tests. As long as you show up to class and do the readings, which are interesting, you shouldn't have a problem.

The class itself is pretty boring, but Professor Lount is a great teacher. He's a very clear lecturer and provides his slides online. There are three exams, non of which are cumulative. The book helps clear things up, but isn't necessary to do well. I would definitely recommend him for this class.

Dr.  is great. He's passionate and energetic, he's incredibly kind and incredibly smart. He teaches you how to think instead of what to think. I felt moved more than once during his lectures. He's difficult to follow though. Don't be afraid to ask for clarification. And don't bother emailing - just knock right on his office door.

I took 4551 & 4555 with him this semester. Attendance isn't mandatory, but it does help a lot to attend. His exams are pretty difficult as well, but as long as you have a general idea of the studies presented in class, you'll be fine. He also has an awesome curve. I failed the 1st exam horribly and still ended up with a B. overall, good prof.
This man is unbelievably smart. I've learned so much from him. If you are looking for an easy A, try something else, but if you want to actually learn something, IS 210 is a great class.

Interesting class. Lectures were sometimes boring, especially if your the type to read before class. Two easy papers. Tests are simple and to the point, consist of equal multiple choice and short answer. Be sure to attend class she gives 2 points per class. I would recommended her. Easy B, only because I didn't go to all lectures

Class was far too much work for a 3 credit hour/3000 level class. I wasn't prepared to spend so much time on it so I ended up with my lowest grade in college ever. He is a passionate teacher but it was so hard to take this class online. Listened to 3+ hours of lectures/week + hours of reading. Tests used Proctorio which is bad for anxious people.
Professor  is great! Nicest dude, really knows his stuff, very good lecturer. Hard to get a hold of sometimes, though.

Super funny guy. Lectures aren't mandatory but are never boring - I would recommend attending but he posts abbreviated recorded lectures that are super helpful as well. His tests can be a bit difficult, though - it's sometimes hard to tell exactly what you need to know versus what is extra information. Regardless, he's wildly entertaining.

Only negative thing you could say about  is that his class seems to attract students who can't help but think their contributions to class discussion are God's gift to man. Favorite professor I've had at OSU and easy A if you attend class and put in a decent amount of effort.

Dr.  is a tough prof, but if you do the readings then you can do well. While there are a lot, they're very instructive on nat'lism and ethnicity. She's a brilliant scholar, and if you are thinking about research then she's a great person to ask for help. Grading is mostly exams plus reading quizzes. You get out of the class what you put in.

Dr. 's class is well organized and an easy-A. However, his lectures can be super long and very boring. He'll talk for 10 minutes about something that could be discussed in 2 minutes. The reading for each week is heavy, but you can get away with skimming. Responsive to emails. Would recommend for an easy GE.
so easy

Great person in general and professor in general, but do not recommend this class to anyone who has bad study habits. Pop Quizzes will sneak up on you. Exams are worded very difficult, so you must study and know what you are learning. Lectures can be long and boring on most days.

likes to facilitate class conversation which can get a little boring, but her exams are easy (you can contribute questions to them and she has buffer questions), and participation points can be made up by posting on the forum. Going to class isn't strictly necessary because she posts slides, but I enjoy it for her helpful examples.
very ethusiastic about teaching

The material is tough, but if you pay CLOSE attention during lecture you should do okay. I'm into this topic so it was probably a bit more interesting for me. He's kind of witty, explains things pretty well for such a complex topic.
She was AMAZING!

A good course to fill your schedule with if you're already slammed. The assignments are very short and she gives guided notes for you to write in while reading the textbook. If you pay attention to the material and put effort into discussions/journals, you're sure to get an A

W/  ATTENDANCE MATTTERS. 5 quizzes (scheduled), 5 attendace & 5 reflections (both not scheduled & taken in class. in my class in the last 4 weeks, which was annoying), & final only 200 points total (not weighted.) He promises hella extra points but only offered like 5 points. He has cool stories from clinical experience. show up & you'll pass.
He is awesome

She is very nice and very smart. She expects things to be in when she says they need to be in. I learned a lot from her but it wasn't really exciting. She talks a lot and shows power points. The movies she shows are great, and the material isn't to hard. The exams are long I suggest studying!!

Pretty straightforward. His study guides aren't 100% of what's going to be on the test, though, so watch out. Labs and projects are all easy - just do them! The tests are kind of hit-or-miss, so study for them. Definitely doable.
Dr.  was a good professor. She would be willing to help, however she is a stickler when it comes to the grammar on papers. But the study guide and quizzes were helpful.
not that bad, never bought the book and got an easy A.
She's pretty nice, does all the lecture through powerpoint. Exams are very tricky.

Brilliant professor... and provided a completely new perspective on psychology that I would've never had unless I took this class. Very beneficial because the field is turning to evidence based practice and he's obviously a strong supporter of it. Personally don't think you should graduate with a psych degree without taking his class

is really one of the best at OSU. His tests are tough but fair, the paper is easy if you follow his instructions and go to him for help, and the reading isn't really necessary. The guy is absolutely brilliant and knows an unbelievable amount about OH politics, you will learn a ton!

If you have the option to take a different GE or 1101H with a different professor take it! The exams are only essays and he gives you the prompts ahead of time. He is a very very harsh grader. There is no rubric and hes okay with giving a large amount of the class Cs and Ds. Dont take this class if youre expecting an easy A.
Online class so I didn't interact with her much. However she seemed nice and the class is easy.

was not my favorite professor. he was entertaining at first, but he began to repeat his stories a lot and let students get off topic. Lectures took longer than they needed to. Not graded on many things (5 attendance, 5 reflections, 5 quizzes, and a final). quizzes were 10 mcq, but were cumulative and some were a bit challenging.

I did not vibe well with him. Most of his lectures were way too long, longer then they needed to be, and we watched about 6 movies that were required for the discussion posts. You will mostly be communicating with the TA assigned to your group. Most of his material is at least two years old. I would recommend taking it with another professor.

The class is comprised of 3 exams, REP assignment and a term paper. Exams are graded very strictly. This did not happen, and after asking to see the breakdown of the grades and get some kind of explanation, I was denied. Disappointed.
best lecturer I've ever had.

Dr. , along with the other head professor for this class, did not support students well throughout the semester. The class felt very disorganized. He was also not very accessible through e-mail or through direct messaging through the course.

If you come to class and pay attention, there is no way you shouldn't get an A even with minimal studying for exams. Easy class, but will be easier the more science knowledge you have. However he isn't the best in the hard science areas and at times he generalizes way too much and gets it wrong, the longer the explanation the more likely its wrong.

Took class online. very boring. out of 500 points 260 are practically given. the rest is the midterm and final..120 each. This class is basically like biology. Material is pretty tricky and test questions are extremely detailed. Carmen discussions are helpful. If you keep up with the reading you'll be fine. I didn't and still got a B+.

If you are interested in going through 5 minutes of slides during class & then discussing current events or his/other students personal & often unrelated experiences, take Curts class. It is a cakewalk, but you learn little to nothing about what you're supposed to be learning. 15-20 page paper at the end of the semester he definitely doesnt read

This was probably one of the hardest political science classes I've taken. The readings were really interesting which I appreciated. Overall though, Professor  was fine but his tests were very difficult and he graded the papers harshly as well. He did curve our grades a little though.

Pretty hard class but totally doable, but like someone else said, it's extremely easy to get the 50 bonus points, and they do matter since your grade is out of 1000. I thought the class was extremely boring, and this is the first class I have ever taken which you could definitely get an A without going to class; Everything you need is online.

This class would be easy if you had the time to put into it but I would advise not to take it with three other classes. Very nit picky about exam questions. I second this comment to a tee: "He doesn't take attendance ... didn't leave much of an impression on me."

Ignores emails asking for help. Homework load is excessive to the point my other classes were affected. Do not take this class if you want your grade to be determined by 4 things. 2 of the grades in this class are done by the TA and the other 2 are a midterm and a final. interesting, relatively easy class

Had him for my psych 1100 and my data analysis course. He's a very reasonable professor. And to all the people that said his tests are extremely hard, it's just because you didn't study. Every class I've had with him had two groups, the ones who studied and averaged an A on tests, and those who didn't and blamed him for their failures.

Mr. is a great teacher who knows his stuff. He is liberal(check fec.gov for who he's donated to) but does a great job hiding it. DO THE READINGS.the exams are multiple choice/essay. he gives the possible 6 essay questions in advance. This class stressed me out the entire semester! Your grade is based on the midterm, final, a book report, and a research project. This class requires a lot of work, but it's doable.

This class was too difficult; I am not sure that he realized it was a GEC and not an upper lever Neuro-biology class! Class seemed interesting but for the same amount of work I put in to getting As in other classes I was getting a D in this one.

THESE REVIEWS DO NOT DO HIM JUSTICE. Class is really not that bad. If you ask him he will tell you exactly what he is looking for on the exams, as long as you memorize that its an easy A. He is probably the funniest professor I have ever had. French Mr. Rogers. I always look forward to going to lecture as they never fail to brighten my day.

After experiencing both Covid and depression and receiving a doctors note for both of these issues, Dr. would not unlock the current modules so that I could catch up and stay current in the course. Instead he forced me to continue doing them in order, even though each module is unrelated to the others. Doesn't seem to care about the students.

Mr. s is tough grader, he gives a 3 papers throughout the semester and a topic and even if you follow the topic he will grade like he is an English professor. she was hard. the tests were even harder. the material was interesting but test material hard. lots of reading and testing on book material. did not like the teacher either.

Pretty good professor, just a boring and tough course. Not much homework but when we did have some it was always easy. Exams are way harder than the HW and you have to put in a lot of effort into understanding the material on your own to get an A/B but its not impossible.

Though Prof.  is an amazingly nice man, I'm not sure if I could stand to sit there for 10 weeks again. The tests and essay were easy, but lectures were not at all helpful to the class. Refers you to sections of the book and spends nearly an hour talking about what poli sci majors should already know-- the political news. nice guy but do avoid
Getting an A would be miraculous with this guy. Way too hard to follow. In lecture, you think you understand what's going on, but when test time rolls around, it's like a foreign languange.

He was a nice guy who explained the concepts really well and made the subject interesting. His exams were straight forward from the material and were not trying to trick or mislead, just test your knowledge

Class grade is based off of online quizzes over lecture material and two papers. We covered less than half the syllabus, a little dissapointing. Dr. Caldiera himself seems like a nice person but individual lectures themselves were dry and didn't explain overall legal reaching principles. a king

about as close to real world political science experience as you can get in a classroom. this guy is top notch in experience, knowledge etc and expects a lot from his students. very direct and open to student concerns, consider yourself lucky if he still has matt scherebath (sp?) as his TA.

The material could be considered difficult to grasp but his lectures, study guides and overall enthusiasm for the material made it incredibly easy to understand/learn. Not a crazy amount of work outside of class, over all really enjoyed his teaching style/enthusiasm for the subject! 10/10 would recommend sense and perception with him!

Excellent. His lectures are very interesting, and he is really laid-back. You have to work for six hours per week with a campaign of your choice and write an essay about it. Do not buy the textbooks; you will never even look at them.
She is so sweet and caring! Her material is super straightforward so exams are too.

Dr.  is great! He is funny and very intelligent without being condescending. I learned a ton from his class. DO go to class, since powerpoints only have bullet points, notes have to be taken in class. Tests are easy, great study guides, pretty much all 4 papers relatively the same. I would definitely take another class with him.

I took Juvenile Delinquency with her and it was awesome! She loves what she teaches and that comes across clearly in her lectures. There are a lot of little assignments on Carmen but they're straightforward and easy. The exams are easy after a quick review of the book chapters. Definitely take this class with her!!
Fell asleep almost every class but he is very passionate about HR. Videos made it bearable and extra credit offered. Tests were specific, definitely need the book
grades very hard, couldn't really help with the essay

I'm really glad I took his class. For some psych majors it might seem a little difficult since there is a good amount of bio/neuroscience, but I enjoyed it a lot. Tbh I literally didn't go to class, went the first week then never showed up again. Also never used the textbook so I wouldn't recommend buying it.

Professor  is an absentee-online professor that does research abroad while facilitating the course. You will never see her, or anyone for that matter in the course. Content is straightforward. Readings are unnecessary, just skim through her powerpoints and you will be fine. Take advantage of the extra credit on weekly quizzes; it will add up!

is actually one of the best teachers I have had at OSU so far. He is extremely clear with what he expects and wants you to be prepared for exams (he has awesome review sheets and a review day). He does not want to trick you and what you see is what you get- study the powerpoint and you'll do great!!
Smart guy, but very unwilling to help in my opinion. If you attend class and do the readings, you should be alright. But don't expect very helpful responses if you email/ask him questions.
Awesome guy, awesome teacher, peal of professing abilities
good luck w this one

Dr.  was a fine professor but she took on more than she could chew with this course. She had to be in charge of 7 different academic papers. Every week we would go over the same things because she couldn't remember what we discussed previously. We would only meet for about ten minutes each week.

Dr.  is a very funny, caring man but the thing that is hard with him is that he talks very fast. His slides are always way too long for him to finish them in one class period, so you're stuck rushing and not getting all of the information he is telling you. Also you will need to read the textbook, he puts random questions on the test.

Can't really depend on his notes, if you read you will be fine though!! This class has a heavy workload! Pat konws what he is talking about but don't depend on him for help, he is really busy and probably will not answer your e-mails!
She was by far the best prof. for this course. She took normally boring material and made it interesting. Her quizzes are challenging but NOBODY should have problems if they read the book.

Easy class. Except huge catch. If you have any traumatic event happen in your life that prevents you from participating as much or asking for an extension, expect zero sympathy and an extremely insensitive response. Just tell student advocacy instead to avoid this issue.
AMAZING teacher. He was funny and down to earth. Highly recommended.
Smartest teacher I ever had at OSU. Make sure you read and go to class. You'll take a million notes. Highly recommend you take his class.
He is incredibly intelligent and international studies 210 was the epitome of a liberal arts education.

Very kind, took 4285 with her last semester, definitely cares about students in and puts effort into prepping for lectures. However, she seems like she has too much on her plate. Syllabus was thrown away, class regularly cancelled, and by the time I had written the final essay, she had gotten rid of the assignment as a whole and ended the class.

4644 is a good class for the sequenced advanced psych class, but I had to study a lot to get good grades. the lectures are pretty boring and when you ask questions in class she usually doesn't even know the answer. there are extra credit opportunities and the homework is easy, but the exams can be tough. overall, its a fair class.

This was a great class. Easy grade if you did the reading, came to class, and followed instructions. And if you do those things you actually learn a lot! What more could you ask for. Some say he picks on students, but its just sarcastic humor and he is actually pretty funny.

The bad reviews are likely from people who didn't go to class and didn't put the time in. Although attendance technically isn't mandatory, you HAVE to go to class to get the notes and content. She is an amazing professor- her lectures are great and she is very eager to help. Very sweet lady. Put the time in, and you will get a good grade!

One of my best professors so far! The only reason I got a B in this class was because I had a few missing assignments from being lazy on my part. Two assignments per week, the quizzes are super easy and open book. The essays are fairly easy as well as long as you understand information. Dr.  was super understanding with the pandemic!

Do not take this class with Dr. . The material of the class is not difficult, however, she makes quizzes/exams much more difficult than they need to be. Her lectures are dry and you must be paying attention 100% of the time to get the needed material for quizzes/exams otherwise you will not find it in the textbook/anywhere else.

Professor  made the material as interesting as he could!! Tests can be tough! So read and re-read the books and his vague lecture outlines! He gets very specific about theories and major experiments discussed in class!

I took Juvenile Delinquency with her and it was amazing! She loves what she teaches and her lectures are very interesting. She uses top hat throughout the class and there are a lot of little assignments on Carmen but they are just reading questions and are easy. The exams are easy after you review the lectures and text book.

Dr.  is very energetic and funny. Makes class enjoyable and entertaining. sometimes she throws candy at us for participating. Lots of easy assignments but you get multiple tries. lots of tophat but they're easy

TAKE THIS CLASS!! Should be required for ALL psych majors! Dr.  is incredibly informative and helpful. The subject material is interesting and sometimes even astonishing. Attend class, because most of the material on the tests comes from lecture. Tests are all essay, but if you attend lecture and do readings and they should be fine!

Really like her as a person, but she can be a little unorganized (probably due to the pandemic) and I had a hard time reachi her outside of class. Sometimes lectures weren't always posted, but the assignments are easy enough to do without really listeni to the lectures anyway. Shes really nice and fun though!

Excellent professor! If you want to learn about Ohio and her politics, there is no better professor to have than  ; its definitely a class that you don't want to miss! His lectures are always informative, relevant and never boring. On a separate note, I read one of his books for another class (Polling and the Public: What Every Citize

I love Doctor . He is kind but also extremely hilarious in his classes. His mixture of self-deprecation as well as his beautifully crafted power points make him my favorite professor I have had yet. Though the lectures are not attendance-mandatory, you don't want to miss them (especially for his random tangents).
great instruction

Dave was the best teacher I have had in a while- always accessible outside of typical hours and really cares about his students. He tries so hard to help his students and is really flexible. He is super knowledgeable about what he does and I respect him a lot. Lectures are kind of boring, but its not that interesting of a class to begin with aahah
A great professor who relates to the students. His Sociology of Gangs class was intriguing and he presented the information in a way that everyone could understand.

Professor DeKay is a great professor, he really cares about stats. If you have the option to take this class or to take another I would highly suggest thinking about how much you like stats. I am not a stats person so I had a really hard time in this class. I also highly suggest going to class, I did not and it really hurt my grade in the end.

Might be the easiest upper-level neuro class OSU offers. Dr.  is great and the material you learn is very useful for the MCAT. Never went to class and studied for exams the night before and got an easy A. She offers extra credit for every exam. Highly recommend using Anki to keep up with the material. VERY EASY A!! TAKE this class.

Dr.  did a great job relating introductory demography with world pop trends/issues.Easy enough if you show up to class, pay attention and study a little bit (imagine that...)The info should be thought provoking to those interested in global demographics.I recommend this course.You're unlikely to encounter this material anywhere else, so LEARN!

Theory can be difficult, this much is true, but sometimes it feels like Prof. MacGilvray makes it as difficult as possible. Class is dragged on by his harsh implementation of the Socratic method, there are no slides/notes so you MUST attend, he gives pop quizzes constantly, and tests are a nightmare. Glad I like this stuff and at least he's nice.

Dr.  is outstanding. Her class is demanding, but it was the most intellectually engaging class I've taken in college. She is wicked smart, accessible outside of class, and is really caring and gives positive feedback. She is overall incredible and so good at guiding class discussion and analyzing the nuances of political theories.

Prob my favorite prof ever! It's not an easy class. Go to it, and listen carefully. He gives the 5 sides of every argument so it's impossible for know his opinion. I learned a lot though, and have used this info in other classes. Also slept through and exam, and he was so sweet about calming me down and letting me make it up.Depends on your interes

His online lectures are amazing & a lot of his quiz questions are phrased word for word on what he said in lecture. Ive never read any of the readings and Ive done fine on his quizzes. His midterm takes a lot of questions from the quizzes so WRITE THEM DOWN. If you do the lectures and take good notes (write exactly what he says) then youre good

He is a great professor and can tell he loves what he does and is more than willing to help you as much as you need. He makes it very hard to fail, if you come to class, ask questions, and do the work he will not let you fail! He is so helpful and is really there to help his students... Pretty much if you fail it is because you don't care! love him
Excellent professor. Exams are straightforward and willing to provide a lot good feedback for the potentially daunting 10-page paper.
He turned a topic I didnt care the slightest about into something accessible and actually pretty interesting. You can tell he cares about making sure his students do well.

A very funny professor who always asks us to "bombard" him with questions and is very quick to respond to emails. He provides full and short lectures on each chapter and puts an emphasis on individual exploration. We had a weekly quiz, discussion posts, questions, journal entry/ activity, and a quiz make-up activity with no exams or tests.
LOTS of reading, but alot of it was redundant.. Lots of material, but a very comprehensive course... Know everything for the midterm and final. Curves well...
Do you Sona studies early, that is the best advice I can give to any student taking intro psych. Dr.  was a great professor, be sure to study, and start studying early!!

I took this class in sp 08. Don't know what the big deal is why people are saying it was hard. You have to read the book!!!! A lot of the test questions come from the book, also I suggest printing the notes before coming to class it helps a lot. I got 90% on all my exams and the avg. was in the 60% range. Do what ur suppose to do and ull get an A!

Professor  is a great guy who always tried to make class enjoyable. He recognized that none of the people in my class were Anthropology majors, and he didnt pretend like the subjects were the most interesting thing in the world. The class was very boring, and the study guides were not very helpful when it came to the 3 exams. Awesome guy!

You can tell he is a caring and nice person, but this is one of the most unorganized courses I have taken. The lecture slides either have overwhelming amounts of information or barely anything other than key terms. Unclear criteria for the assignments and paper as well. Pretty easy to pass but not a great time.

Class had zero quizzes or tests. Had a reading with summary and opinion article due every week and two essays.  seems to be very smart and wants everyone to succeed. Class got boring at times but he recognizes that we have many more difficult classes.

Took Stereotype and Prejudice. There are some basic online notes, so you have to show up to class and pay attention. 4 hard tests and optional cumulative final to replace your lowest exam. This class shouldve been easier but the amount of info was too much and he describes all these studies in a difficult way. Nice guy but hard class.

He's one of the best teachers for neuroscience. He's a great lecturer. One bad thing about the class is that there is not enough points in the class. If you don't attend lecture, you'll probably fair. Be warned, his exam questions can be convoluted.

This class is not worth the amount of work he assigns. Every week you have to read two thirty-page academic papers and 4 or five book chapters. For exams, he gives you ten essay prompts based on these papers. you have to prepare your evidence for all of them and he'll ask for two. You basically have to write 30 essays for this class.

The only grade in the class is the midterm and final, which isn't an easy exam, but he does curve it! I would take it with someone else if possible, but have learned a lot. It is an intro level course, but is much harder than that. Other students in my class do not like him, but I do not mind him.

You'll be doing a lot of reading for the class, but the articles are pretty interesting. Presentations in class and discussions are interesting but can get pretty heated if a few people start arguing. He always wants to hear your opinion, which is pretty cool.
Very informative class, would definitely reccommend taking.

Dr.  is a brilliant psychologist.The only downside is that is attempting to teach statistics to psychology kids, who can't do math to save their lives.His class is challenging.SAS takes a while to learn, and the homeworks are tedious.Model your assignments after his notes. Most folks are just bitter about their grade, should've tried harder.

If you love the brain, you will love Dr. 's class! His class was by far my favorite and I looked forward to going every time. I recommend taking advantage his office hours, because he is amazing to get to know. To succeed in this class, attend every class and take as many notes as you can for reference on some of the vague slides.
Literally, she is the best.

I had Professor  for Psych 501 and H613. He is a phenomenal professor and his lectures are awesome (I hated missing his class). His courses are definitely no cake walk, but you can really learn a lot from him. He is also very fair with grades and will say that he prefers to reward people for taking hard classes (like his).

I'm split, the exams got progressively harder, he's not a bad prof. online notes are pretty clear and so is he, I just wish his exams weren't so hard, i don't feel that I learned the mixed/multiANOVA's very well, the "labs" kinda help you use SPSS but they aren't structured well, HW takes about 20 min max with SPSS, 7/10
neutral

I cannot rave enough about Professor . Best teacher I have had in my 4 years at OSU. He just gets it. He is so clear about his expectations and his exam questions are taken straight from lecture notes. Also super easy to reach if you do not understand something. Definitely take him especially if you are a psych student!

Prof  is so smart and knowledgable. I learned sooo much from this class and it was super interesting. It's not the easiest class but if you put in a decent amount of effort there's no reason you shouldn't succeed.

If you like political science, he is the professor for you. But if you are just looking for a GE, there are better options. Lectures can be incredibly boring, but tests are easy & he supplies study guides.

Lectures from minute to minute of 1 hr 20 min class. No breaks. Have to take many notes during class. Uses unfamiliar examples so it is difficult to understand. Decision making is a statistic class. NOT a psychology class. It has almost nothing to do with psychology. Do not take if you are a senior and wanting a low work class.

Dr.  is by far one of the most incredible professors you will ever have. He is a tough professor, but it was 100% worth every second. He is absolutely hilarious and you learn so much. Take him if you have the chance

Grade 3 test, each worth 1/3 of the Grade. Gets harder each test, and the last essay question you literally have nowhere to copy from but to think hard for yourself. Enjoyed it so much. Didnt do many the reading, but make sure to attend and take notes.

Dr.  is extremely knowledgeable on many topics and conceptualizes political theory like none other. The class however, is extremely reading-intensive, and it can be very easy to fall behind in the difficulty and the amount of readings given. Dont take her class if youre looking for an easy grade-booster, youll get the opposite.

Dr. is extremely knowledgeable about the subject matter..but at times there is so much info that it becomes overwhelming..generally a nice man...and VERY lingwinded..probablly becuase he loves the subject matter..first part of class was tough if you don't really have a background in the subject..but latter half of class is easy..final paper

I love , she's helpful and understanding and unlike some teachers you'll get she really cares about her students learning the material. Had a blast in the class and I am totally going to take her again.

This is a 3000 level undergrad course that is formatted like an advanced graduate level class. We can rely only on empirical articles to piece together class concepts. There is no textbook. The slides are minimally helpful, and the professor is hard to reach. If you want a challenge, great. But know what you're signing up for. I sure didn't.

She is clearly passionate about the subject and knows what she's talking about. The class material was very interesting. The tests were difficult but not impossible, and I always ended up doing better than I expected. The book for the class is interesting but I smed it, and I didn't use the textbook except for the final paper.
I really loved this class! Would highly recommend going on the police ride along. gives a lot of extra credit and tests are taken online

I really enjoyed this class. Dr.  is a little disorganized but his lectures are interesting. His tests are from both the book and the lecture material and he loves testing on statistics. If you're interested in psychopathology you'll like the class. I recommend it.

I didn't know what I was doing on the exams and I still got an A on all of them. It's an easy class, but she makes the information harder than it needs to be. If you want an easy stats class, take her.
Assigns a lot of work, but exams and grading are very reasonable. If you get to know her, you'll think she's fabulous.

Like a lot of grad classes in psych I found this one to not be very informative. I learned a few things. Some of it was repeated from lower level courses, or the lectures were very mundane. Graded items are three presentations, and short weekly response paper to articles, which are difficult to read. Make sure your presentations are very detailed.

The people saying that this class was bad obviously did not know what they were getting into, and that is not Dr. 's fault. It's a 5000 lvl psych course, which at OSU, generally means group projects/presenting. Should have looked into it before you signed up. Anyway, Dr.  is fantastic & wants you to succeed. Do the work and you'll do great.
She made class fun and interesting.

Dr. 's class wasn't difficult and he is an extremely nice person. I just wanted to comment to warn that if you want to get excited about Sociology, this is not the professor to take. His lectures were so hard to sit through. Don't bother buying the textbook, but you need the reader! Take the essay version of the exams.
Class was pretty difficult. E is pretty smart, very wordy, but there's some good information. Lots of readings required. Difficult to take notes.

Political science isn't exactly my strongest subject, but this was wasn't horribly difficult. If you really understand political science, the lectures probably aren't necessary. The information is all on the powerpoints, but I thought some of his lectures were really interesting. Tests were fair, and study guides were given out before each one.
Notes are not online so you have to go to class if you want the notes, which are a lot! You will need the book.

I have taken a few classes with . She's a very good teacher and has lots of ways to make lecture not so boring. Her tests are tough though. You really need to study and understand what's going on. Her classes are interesting but can be tough. It's really not a slack-off kind of class.

The exams are written (no multiple choice). The exams are approximately 20 questions long and we only had 55 minutes to complete. Wording on exams can be confusing. There are two textbooks: she pulls from both. Lectures either make you feel like you have a handle on topics, or you have no idea what is going on. She posts incomplete lecture slides.

gives lectures with really interesting examples (often old psych experiments) and is funny and a very cheesy way. His tests are fair but have some questions that you would only know from in-class lectures. He had a few HW articles with short quizzes that were really just checking if you read the article.
Really really cool person. She's a full bright scholar and has been around the world so she really knows her stuff.

Dr.  is a very competent researcher - but not a phenomenal lecturer. His tests can be really tough and the material isn't always explained effectively. He implements a curved grading scale on assignments because most people don't do very well. Not that recommended unless you really want to learn about Attitudes and Persuasion.

SO many in class assignments, hard tests, but she was a good teacher and stats was required for a psych degree so if you have to take this class then I would take it with her because I was actually able to understand the content
I was really inspired by her! She makes things really interesting and she's really easy to talk to! I want to look into the social stratification minor, that's how interesting she made the class!

Nice Prof. Easy A. Daily attendance not necessary but there are random pop quizzes (10) on readingclass activities throughout the semester. Study guides tell you exactly what info from the power points for the midterm and final. Group projectpaper was a huge pain.

Professor Lount is solid. He's passionate about what he teaches. Class is a little boring, but he splices videos in every now and then to keep the content fresh. My only complaint is about some of the overly-specific test questions; if you don't read the book and pick up on minute details, it's easy to miss some of the ones he asks. Still got an A.
Amazing professor!!! all that needs to be said
Class is extremely overwhelming with material. Not clear instructions given. You have to retake material until you get a 90% . So much to do for a 3320 class. Do not recommend at all

If you do decide to take his class, make sure you show up for every class because he makes attendance basically 50% of your grade. There's no debating your missed attendance situation unless it's severe enough to warrant a doctor's note.
I think she is a great professor!!! Lots of information but she tries to make it easier. Quite a few extra credits which made me get an A-!

Ben is an absolutely amazing professor. He cares about his students SO much and is incredibly understanding of mental health. This class has a lot of readings, but you can get away with skimming them as long as you pay attention to his lectures.

He doesn't post anything online so don't lose your syllabus. He doesn't remind you to do the REP even once so if you lose your one paper copy of the syllabus, you won't know how to do it and your grade will drop 10%. Exams are easy just do the "review" things and don't bother studying anything else.

Dr.  is amazing! He is incredibly passionate about Psychology and his passion is contagious. His wit and accent keep you engaged during lecture. He is quite a storyteller, and he treats the history of psychology as such. Exams are primarily identification, association, and essay-based, which is refreshing after taking tons of Scantrons.

Dr.  is a very kind lecturer, and I enjoyed Behavioral Neuro! The notes are extremely long, however, and tests are difficult with little time to complete. If you are struggling, Dr.  is a great person to access and is understanding. The coursework is very time consuming, but if youre interested in the topics then its really not horrible.

is special in that he is smart and knows what he's talking about and he's good at teaching. Make sure to take notes on the reader as you go, it will make your life a lot easier around midterms and finals. He doesn't give tests, only two essay exams and a project.

COVID-19: Class was asynchronous, gave lots of opportunities for points via quizzes, assignments, discussion boards. Great lecturer, enthusiastic delivery of material. Assignments could be busy work and somewhat insulting to collegiate level students (scavenger hunt activities?), but fine for the points. Be prepared to keep up with lectures.

I realyl liked the class because I found the material very interesting but Dr.  made it more difficult to get an A because the only grades were the 4 exams (no extra credit). You can tell he likes teaching, and he is good at explaining everything, but he does like to rant, and it's important to take notes on EVERYTHING because it is tested on

Very difficult- I flew through 701 but almost didnt pass this course. Notes seem fairly straightforward but tests can seem overwhelming. Be sure to understand the notes instead of just memorizing or you'll be out of luck on the exams. Failed a large portion of the class.
He was an Amazing teacher; very informative and the class was a breeze (very easy)

Dr.  is extremely nice and down to Earth. Her lectures are interesting, and she provides powerpoint notes for you to print and bring to class with you. She re-reads definitions three times, so you don't miss a thing. She doesn't over-complicate things either. She doesn't take attendance, but if you don't go to class you'll miss a lot.

Dr.  is brilliant, but her class is way harder than it has to be. Super difficult reading quizzes, and lots of stuff on tests that were hardly covered. Interesting class, but I definitely would not take it again.

Very solid professor. Super nice and funny little jokes here and there to keep the class awake. Definitely go to class, the powerpoints dont have enough text to get by just downloading them and not paying any attention. Also, in-class tophat is pretty much just participation points. Study a couple days in advance for exams and youll be fine.
He was great! Loved the class. He is very energetic and makes the topics interesting. Take his class!!

The professor is a nice guy but he talks so much that you will be confused I promise you. Also the majority of your grade will be based on these three group projects so pray you get a good group. I had a great group and we struggled together to get through each assignment.

far too in-depth for a 200 level class. The readings were long, not discussed, and not chronologically relevant to the day's lecture. The man is brilliant, but he expects you to be also in how he constructs his test questions. Tons of material overall. Avoid.

He's very passionate and clearly knowledgeable about what he teaches and expects you to thoroughly engage with the content. Hes very understanding too. Most grades are from reading quizzes and a couple papers throughout. Shouldn't take this class unless youre genuinely interested in foreign policy, but if you are and you care youll love it.
online is easy just command find through powerpoints mostly

This class was by far the greatest class I've ever taken in my 4yrs of undergrad. Dr.  IS constructivism. Don't skip class, he only teaches one course and every lecture is incredibly interesting, insightful, organized and beneficial. Soak up all you can from this guy, he is literally the most interesting and intelligent human on the planet!

This dude is awesome. This is my second class with him and he did not disappoint. This isnt an easy course (none of his courses are), but if you put in a little effort, its not a problem. He wants everyone to form their own opinions and ideas about the course material!

Dr.  was a pretty chill professor. There aren't many tests and there was never homework besides the term paper/presentation, but he was generally a pretty easy grader as long as you show that you know the information decently well. Tip: start working on the study guides as you go through the chapters instead of cramming it in before the exam.

I don't know if it's just the way she taught it, but I hardly understood any of the material for this class. However, I still got an A on every exam and in the class. That doesn't make sense, obviously, but I guess if you want a relatively easy A class, go ahead and take this one!

He's a great guy who loves this topic, but you don't actually get through much content in the class because he talks about it all a little too much. Graded by three response papers, two exams, one final paper, and some reading quizzes. You really need to do the reading and it's very unclear exactly what he expects you to do in the papers.

She is really nice and although the class can get boring at times, she tries to make it interesting. She takes attendance at the end of every class. There is a lot of reading every night, but if you listen and take good notes, reading isn't entirely necessary.

He is an amazing person. Really nice and understanding. He cares for all of his students, and encourages people to visit him outside of class to talk about their interests. His lectures, however, were monotone and it was easy to fall asleep through. Thankfully, he is very clear with what he expects the students to know on both exams and papers.
This is his first semester teaching here. He is not as bad as the previous review. Need to take notes, slides are posted online but notes are needed to get decent grades on quizzes. No tests!

The first week you may think that since there is no homework, you can skip and pass no problem... you'd be wrong. The detail in the lectures that he provides cannot be made up by attending the review seasons. Theres is no way to fake your way through his tests. Lots of reading required but it becomes easier to understand after discussion.
She is extremely nice and very helpful. She gives a lot of extra credit. This class would be a lot easier if you read the textbook.

Tough but fair, one of my best professors yet! You will not regret taking his class, but you should regret not taking the time to learn the material. Ignore reviews on his accent, he is well spoken. He is fair and upfront about the grading scale, but it is tough. I found he is the best instructor of PSYCH3312. Also READ READ READ, the book is good!

Professor  is a fantastic instructor but also an incredibly tough grader. Class is made up entirely of exams, so don't fail any because otherwise, you'll fail the course. He also offers little to no extra credit, so don't forget to prep for exams because they're your only source of redemption.
is a nice guy but grades difficultly. He assigns much work to his honors students and expects them to work accordingly. Class excitement level is determined by students.

This class is not impossible, and it is very interesting and intellectually stimulating. There is no homework, but there are 4 tests that require a lot of studying. It is difficult to take notes, but I recommend recording the lectures and taking notes at your own pace. I left this class with more knowledge and an actual understanding of the concept
She knows her stuff. Class is challenging, interesting.
he took this class waaaay too seriously for a 100 level Comm class. offers no extra credit and averages your exams and quizzes instead of taking your better score

This class isn't difficult If you have a strong foundation in math if you don't I would recommend rectifying those problems before taking this class. Study and you will do well. He is very understanding.

The material was tough, the lectures were not helpful at all but attendance is mandatory. He takes attendance on this website that you have to pay $20 for. The 3 exams, which make up your course grade, are extremely tough. Sometimes one word can be the difference between a right and wrong answer. Textbook not necessary. Make study guides of cases.
This is the third class I have taken with Dr. . Although you have to work for an A, her classes will teach you a ton and she is extremely intelligent and well respected in her field.
I loved her class i took it last year and i plan to talk the inside out course soon. shes very nice and understanding :) her test are fair.

I was terrified going into this class because I read reviews, but Dr. Edwards was nowhere near as tough as I expected. Class is heavily based on daily readings and discussion, so definitely go to class and participate if you want a good grade. Not a lot of grades but stay on top of the work, pay attention to lectures, and study and you'll be fine.

He's really cool, passionate and interesting. Recommend him. His lecture consists of: 50% jokes (ehich I really cannot always get) and cute puppies or some other animals, 20% about personal experience, mostly academic experience, 30% real lecture which is awesome. Class is not hard, just pay attention and rebiew carefully, then you'll ace it.

Really good teacher. Just come to class and take notes. EVERYTHING that will be on the test will be in his power points! Since he doesn't put his p.p. online, you have to come to class to get the notes. Plus he explains things as he goes so just go to class!! He can go a little quickly through the p.p. so just speak up and he will go back.

Multiple choice exams VERY difficult. An awesome class none the less. I learned a lot. He once said that even if you get a C in his class you will know more than the average layman about PD and AD, and he's right.

It is evident that Dr.  has a really good heart and is very knowledgeable on the subject of environmental health, but he doesn't do a great job translating this knowledge in an understandable manner to his students. Don't let this scare you, because it's not hard to do well in the class, but beware that you probably wont learn much from him.

Not sure why he has such low ratings. I think   is an amazing professor. Throughly explains the material is a way for students to understand. He is one of the best lecturing professors I have encountered so far at OSU. He doesnt just read from the slides like most professors and really engages with the class.
She is a really funny person. I had a lot of fun in this class. It was interesting and she made the class atmosphere laid back and comfortable.
I LOVED DR !! I always recommend him to anyone. I just studied the slides and I was fine. He's really not out to get you.
I loved this class!

Class was a very interesting, although it was pretty much impossible to take notes during the lectures as he just stood up there and spoke freely. He has a lot of experience and deserves a lot of respect for his knowledge on the subject. At the end of the class you play a foreign policy gamet that is a lot of fun. The exams are no joke.
