He was super awesome. He truly wanted to help us learn and gave us access to all the lectures. Study the powerpoints, learn some vocab, and apply it to the essays. Super easy, cut and dry.

Had her for an inside out course... Very interesting class and she gave everyone an equal opportunity to participate. There were a ton of papers, but no tests or final. I would definitely recommend her to anyone. I actually plan on taking another class of hers

Professor  has long lectures, and the beginning of the course was difficult. The labs are almost all dissection, so if you have a weak stomach, I do not recommend this course. There was a lot of group projects at the end of the semester that can make or break your grade, choose your lab partners wisely.
Great instructor

Easy as pie class that's actually really interesting. For the exams, Don't bother with the slides (as he never goes over them), just study the definitions in the book and you'll ace the class. Essay paper is a bit long, but really that hard if you know how to write and have a lot of references (which is not hard with online stuff)
She is seriously an awesome teacher

turns complex hazy topics into something all students can understand. And he manages to do this with humor and interest. He is helpful and loves asking students for opinions. Exams questions are given beforehand but the grading is slightly subjective and tough. Take thorough notes on the computer and you can get by skimming the readings.

The class was awesome. It got a little long winded being a 1:48 lecture 2x a week, but he let us take breaks to keep us from getting too restless. He makes the content clear and answers all questions pretty quickly.
Very great professor

Easy tests, engaging lecture (for the material)- there's lots of videos and comics. If you do the study guide for each exam you will be fine. You can also drop one exam making the final optional! Easiest class a neuro major at OSU will ever take.

Dr.  was awesome. Although I was not interested in the course content and only had to take it for my major, he made it not horrible throughout the semester. He was always willing to go out of his way to help, and also mentioned he will likely make his in person exams open notes. You can tell his enthusiasm on teaching the subject

Class was relatively easy. Lectures are somewhat boring, but his PowerPoints are incredibly useful. The exams come straight from them. Make sure you pay attention in class because there will be exam questions that cover material that he vocalizes.

I took this class because I had interest and it fulfilled my GEC requirement. However she went a lot more indepth and made it much harder than it needed to be. While it was interesting it was extremely difficult. I read the book and attended every class and still struggled.
Dr.  is one of the best professors you will have at OSU. She is intelligent, engaging, understanding, and hilarious. Show up to class, take some notes, and you'll get an A.

I went to one class. I read the book and did his practice problems. Got an A. The material was far too easy for him to bother teaching, and he recycles his exams. It seemed to me he didn't care--he had more important classes to worry about.
You just show up for lecture, and have two tests and homework assignments. Participation is a big thing. He tends to not be so clear, because he side tracks a lot.

Do not take public health data analytics. It was unclear and unorganized, though it was made sure that attendance was taken every class. They assume everyone who takes this class knows R and has the background knowledge of a math major. Those who do not meet those criteria will struggle immensely, and you will not get help when you ask questions.

Dr.  definitely cares about his students success. The quizzes were easy and online. But the tests could be tricky. Just make sure to know the material well and this class should be an easy A. The lectures could be boring, but that happens with any subject.
Class was unorganized and lectures were not engaging.

The sociology class I took was half online and half in class. Very easy class.  will literally do everything she can to help you out with grades. Honestly there is no reason that anyone should get less than a B in this class.
Best teacher I've ever had.

Really great class, i took Welfare because i couldn't fit the class i really wanted in there but i am truly glad i took this class! VERY eye opening class!   is a very great teacher who knows everything about welfare and politics in Europe. I highly encourage this class and I highly encourage taking this teacher. 2 midterms and debate
She has been here a few years, people say she is getting better. I wish she was organized (even a little bit).
Rambles during lecture, doesn't facilitate effective in-class discussions, no real course structure.

Initially, this class was extremely hard. However, once I got the hang of the style of quizzes and exams, it wasn't bad at all. There is a MAJOR curve (currently 80% and above is an A), and  and the TA's understand you are in other classes. I have never taken a political science class before and I learned many things about war and data.
Straight forward class: midterm, final, and paper
This guy is fantastic. He is very helpful, and I would take anything he teaches.

Lectures are sometimes boring but if you pay attention and take notes in lecture you'll do well on the exams. Reading quizzes are not hard because he goes over reading materials during lecture so even if you don't actually read you'll still get full points on the quizzes.

is an awesome prof. Many of the classes were just class discussions based on topics like affirmative action, juries, eyewitness testimonies, etc. Very funny and, if you actually show up to lecture, the tests are extremely straight forward. Posts slides on Carmen, but they don't have much info so you have to go to lecture, but he makes them fun
Professor  is a really cool dude if you talk to him outside of class, the assignments aren't hard once you realize they all build on each other and are repetitive. Midterms and finals are open book.

was a good professor and a nice person. He was very considerate about work and flexible with deadlines. He would go off topic somewhat frequently in his lectures. This class was very easy if you went to class and took decent notes. For the "exams," I recommend just skimming the textbook and looking at the notes you have taken.

lecture heavy. take good notes. exams are tough but it is a 4000 level course- it is expected. He's nice, and very caring. Even though his lectures are heavy he doesn't make it boring- seems to really care for his students

Lectures are super heavy like 50-90 slides but he never finishes most of them. Quizzes and readings are easy but the exams are very difficult. My exam grades did not reflect the rest of my grades. He seems really caring but he makes  too many mistakes on his own exams. I would not recommend. This class was the definition of stress.

I took Cognitive Neuro with Prof. . I really enjoyed this class! The material was very engaging when the content could have easily been very dry. I appreciate the fact that she was so open to feedback. I also appreciated the learning aids (videos, demonstrations, etc.) she provided that helped the material sink in.
Very Knowledgable, Good amount of work.. had to write a 20-25 page paper for the final. However easy grader, and if you read and do the work you should be fine

legit a dad figure. Such a great guy. I will take any class he offers because he makes class so much fun. not only is it fun, he makes neuroscience easy to understand and is always super helpful. He tries to make his class a "sanctuary" and it really is. Seriously though, love this guy. You won't regret taking his class.

The class is relatively easy with only two exams (take the essay versions and you can bring in outlines on the day of the exam). There's in-class activities for a grade, so you have to show up to class. The lectures are a little boring, but overall the class is an easy A.

Professor  was really interesting, but there was a ton of reading in the course, like a ton. He had us submit our notes for that reading, so there is no getting out of it. It is a good class though. I wish there had been areas touched on more in depth, but its an intro psych course so I can't expect that much. He allowed it to feel personal.
is an awesome prof and she's cool too

You really don't need to go to lecture because he just derives equations and it makes everything seem so confusing. If you just do the homework and make sure you understand it all you are truly guaranteed an A on the exams.

Good teacher, learned a lot. He stands up there and talks about advertising in general and doesn't really teach you about the notes. DON'T buy the book. The notes he posts on Carmen are all you really need to study for the two tests. 3 discussion posts per week and Friday videos instead of class plus a 10 page paper that was on an advertising topic
If you do the basics, go to class, read etc, you'll get a decent grade. Lectures were usually interesting, sometimes humorous. He is really into what he's teaching.

There were only 3 assignments in the course. Took the entire semester to grade 1out of the 3 assignments. Second grade was automatically generated from one of the 2 exams. This class was extremely stressful.

I actually enjoyed this class with Professor . His exams are pretty easy as long as you read the chapters and attend class. Complete the critical thinking questions and it is hard to get a bad grade in this class. He knows what he's talking about and invites you on jail visits with his higher level classes! I'd take a class with him again

is excellent, he really cares about his students, and is funny in class. I wasn't the biggest fan of the class, but that is not fault of his -- he is very accommodating and his grading rubrics are pretty clear for both papers and exams. Lots of reading, but he does a great job clarifying confusing readings. A fairly easy A given the work.

She is a good teacher. Likes to talk a lot and gets everyone involved. She is a tough grader on her exams but easy with the papers. You have to do a ton of work in this class and must show interest or she won't give you the grade you deserve. She is fair, but if you don't like to read and write, avoid her class. Lots of discussions (10%) of grade.
good prof

She was okay. 2 midterm exams (worth 60% total 30% for each. But if you do bad on the 1st exam she will let you change the weight to 20% 40%) attendance is a part of grade and there is no final exam,there is a debate. but you get to sign up to be either a debater(no paper), brief writer (7 page paper), or judge (7 page paper). Easy class.

Good professor but takes forever to grade. Let's you submit things a week early to get feedback. Lectures are good, but slides are confusing if you don't go to class. Good professor if you go to class and don't procrastinate its a great class!
Dr.  is the best. Very intelligent, yet a great teacher as well. Learned a lot from him

Really nice guy and he really wants you to do well. Very clear and interesting lecturer but also puts everything online. The paper was over a long period of time and in section so it guarantees a good grade. And the final exam was the easiest thing I have ever taken in college I was shocked. Highly recommend. (He also brings dogs to class!)

Dr.  was pretty middle of the road for me. The class was really dry even for someone who loves Political Science, but she's super straightforward about what she wants you to know and what the exams will look like. Don't take this if you aren't interested in PoliSci, but if you are you should find this relatively easy.

Dr.  is a very nice guy who is interested in his field BUT I would caution you not to take the class. He uses outdated materials and information. If you choose to take the course make sure that you read the textbook cover to cover and write down every random statistic he says in class.
Good course. Didn't want to take stats, but he makes it enjoyable.

Dr.  is one of the most kind and caring professors I've had at OSU. He does not use lecture slides, which is an adjustment at first, but is very engaging in class. His course was no cakewalk and the material bordered on dull at times, but it wasn't bad if you pay attention and study for exams.

Professor  is obviously passionate about his field and is eager to express his passion to students. Sometimes forgets that students don't know his books as well as he does, but offers opportunities for comments and suggestions which is awesome. If you like a little philosophy and literature in your poli sci take this class :)

Great dude, and a great lecturer. Took this class online asynchronously and still felt connected with him. Definitely not afraid to be opinionated but keeps class pretty light. Lectures were decently long (1-2 hours/week) plus documentaries were often assigned and you had to read a 30 pg-ish long chapter/week, but it was skimmable. 10/10 prof
You will only get out of the class what you put into it but the professor is very knowledgeable and ready to answer every question. Also very good-looking.

Great professor that cares about his student and the material that he teaches. Make sure you come to class, pay attention, and be engaged and that will get you majority of the way and DO NOT neglect reading each of the chapters or else you'll regret it. Only downside is that he doesn't nessciarily give study guides for his exams.
She is the best!

331 is not that hard. A lot of people are complaining, but I don't know why. I never read the book; I just went to class and studied the notes and got A's on both midterms and final. He curves A LOT, and is very generous w/ grading in my opinion. He is really helpful- offers several review sessions. Take his class; it's not that bad

I loved this class! All essays, long and hard but if you attend class, you will be fine and you will have the choice to not take the final. Which I think was the best news ever! The material is very interesting and he makes the class so much fun. He is very funny. Take this class, you will love it.

Dr.  is one of the most well-respected political scientists of our generation. Firstly, he is the father of the constructivists school of thought in international relations. Second, he is so well-versed it will astound you. He is very helpful and welcomes visitors to his office hours. Google him and bow down to his greatness. Take his class.

Honors sociology is a class that I expected to be easy, but in reality, Dr. Edwards is a very hard grader, and it was difficult to scrape by with an A-. Biggest advice: Do the extra credit presentation. You have to email her to sign up. Its on the syllabus but she won't tell you, so be ready! Also, participate a lot and go to lecture. It matters!

is one of those professors I will never forget. Not only are they well educated in the topic they are lecturing on, but it is very apparent that they are passionate about it as well. Their lectures are very fast paced, but that just further illustrates that they love what they do. I would take them again in a heart beat!

3 out of 4 exams are graded and 10 out of 12 discussion posts are graded, and that is it! You will get full points on discussion posts as long as you write it. Exams are not too easy but never too hard, and you can skip final.

w/ , ATTENDANCE MATTERS. I didnt like 's class because lack points (nothing is weighted). 200 points in total, 5 quizzes, 5 attendance and reflections (separate things primarily taken in the last 4 weeks of the semester), and the final. Everything is cumulative. With that said, if you attend and pay attention, you'll pass also cool stories.

I absolutely love  . I took his course in the midst of COVID and he was really understanding with everything going on. If you have the option, 10/10 recommend him. Make sure you read and study, and you'll pass.

is a very knowledgeable guy, worked in the State Dept and clearly has had practical experience with his subject. Still, he seems to genuinely enjoy teaching. Get to participate in a fun diplomatic "game" in second half of class. Midterm and final require lots of preparation, reading. Difficult class, but worth it.

Show up and listen to what she says and you pass. Her review sheets are spot on with her exams. If you can answer the questions on the review sheets your golden, also her exams are very simple and easy to understand all you have to do is just study.

Had Chip for Political Comm, never had him for a pre-req course. I loved his class though. Interesting, intense material. People think he's tough, but guess what: he treats his students like adults and wants to make class a discussion, not a lecture. Considerable reading and discussion to expect, but absolutely a get out what you put in course.
he even made the tests fun because of extra credit questions like, "guess what song he listens to while jogging and why"
Very easy class. She was a good lecturer however could get very off-topic fast.

Took this class during the times of Covid so it was all online with pre recorded lectures. I found it very difficult to pay attention during these lectures especially when each module had at least 10 lecture videos. Professor  seems like a great professor, but I wish she would have cut students a little slack during these hard times.

A sweet,Lovely woman, shes really a gem and wants all her students to succeed. Show up to class, all the tests are based on the readings and lecture notes. If you want an A,SHOW UP to class. The material is hard to follow but if you ask for her help she will make sure you have a clear understanding of the material. The tests r all multiple choice

Class was required for my major but very interesting and easy to stay engaged, gave lots of real world examples to make topics clear, if you ever have a question, email her and she'll respond right away

He's an eccentric and funny guy with excellent music taste. Initially, I was intimidated and scared for my wellbeing in this class, but because he's very good at explaining and teaching, I ended up doing very well. He also gives good feedback if you meet with him during office hours.

He's a good teacher who used to serve as a UN Diplomat under old Bush. His foreign relations class is excellent, he's very dedicated to helping students, and his real life experiences make for a very intersting and informative class. Wish he taught more

a is a wonderful person, but she is not the best professor. She covered the topics adequately, but her lectures were out of date and often centered around Dateline or 60 Minutes videos from the 80s and 90s. Her exams are very easy if you go to class, and she provides the quiz questions in advance so you can prepare.
Very sweet woman. Extremely helpful. Decently interesting class.
Unclear directions and whimsical grading system. Assignment instructions do not match how they are graded.

Slept through lectures, was barely awake for recitations. still got an A. here's how: BOOKS never read it, go to lectures and wake up for in-class writings, also attend recitation, 3 real easy essays that were max 2 pages. boom you got 50%. 1 mid term and final average 87 on multiple choice exams

She obviously knows what she is talking about in regards to the class. However, students did not know that much, and she was not super clear in what was expected. Multiple times I got points taken off for things I would have done if I would have been told to do so. Also, attendance "wasn't mandatory", but she did random attendance checks.
Best class ever.
His exams are very difficult; for a GEC this class is WAY too hard.
This is a very interesting class. I definitely learned a lot, but this is also a difficult class. It takes a lot of work, but it's well worth it.

Man I didn't expect his rating to be so low here... I've had difficult profs but he is definitely not one of them. Detailed study guide, well prepared & organized lecture & materials. On the overlapped content with my PSYCH3513, Dr. 's explanation is better. He is one of the few professors that can catch my attention throughout the lectures.

I would recommend taking Dr.  for an upper level neuro class! She is really fun and assignments are pretty easy. Three group projects throughout the semester, but all very manageable. She's very accessible outside of class and fair grader with clear expectations.

I took the Honors version of the course, easy A. He takes participation credit sometimes but you'll get it if you're there. No need for the Henslin book, you only need the reader. Sit back, survive the lecture and this class is a breeze. He's extremely knowledgeable on the subject, just not the most exciting.

No rubrics are given for papers or assignments and lectures are very unclear. Do not expect any clarity or meaningful communication, you are on your own. She offers a good amount of extra credit, so pulling an A isn't too hard.
Amazing professor. Would definitely recommend. Take him!!!!
My favorite professor! Convinced me to become a Psychology major!
Great class, I learned a lot. He really makes you think critically ! A nice guy too.

He's really passionate about psychology so lectures are pretty engaging. A lot of the material you need to know comes from the book, so you should stay on top of textbook reading. For studying DEFINITELY DEFINITELY do the review questions, from each module that are in carmen, the questions really are similar to the tests. Absolutely do the REP xtra

This class is not as bad as it may seem. He is a practicing psychologist so he lectures on what he thinks is interesting and then you are responsible for what is in the book for the exam. He loves statistics so pay close attention to them while your taking book notes. He also gives a pretty big curve which helps a lot. I got an A fairly easily.

psych 320 is harder than regular stats, but prof.  put the notes online, always explained things carefully, and even had a low key quirky sense of humor. he made a boring subject enjoyable and spent plenty of class time working us through problems that would be on the tests - super helpful!!

Professor  is amazing. He is incredibly organized and communicates the subject matter extremely clearly. He allows ample time for participation also. While you need to study and do the readings to get good grades on the exams, the class is definitely well worth it. I have learned much more about international theory from . Take his class!

Dr. 's cognitive psych class is literally the easiest class I've ever taken. Papers are practically for participation because she's not looking for the most beautiful piece of art, and all 5 online quizzes have 2 attempts to get it right. Homework is super easy too. Least amount of work I've ever had for a class in college.

I had her for this course and Prisons & Jails, both really easy classes with clear expectations. 3 exams, small assignments (1-2 pages) and one presentation (powerpoint) of your choice. Easy grader and she's really funny.

No doubt that Rick knows the material like the back of his hand. However, the lectures have little to no structure. Actively take notes to try to piece it all together. Exams are difficult and hard to prepare for. Definitely read the book before class; he likes to randomly call on people. In-class simulations were fun. Not an easy-A, but an easy-B.
MacEachern made quality control way more interesting than expected.

Class lectures can be very dry if you're not into Polisci. He is very laid back and it shows in the class. There are only two grades in the class. A midterm and final. Both are essays that he gives you ahead of time and grades them with a ton of leniency. He is a realist and not afraid to share his opinion

Easily one of the nicest people I've met and he cares a lot about his students and the subject. You absolutely have to go to class to do well, his lecture slides he posts are very vague if you don't have your own notes from him elaborating. There is a lot of information too and you have to study a lot and hard to understand it all.

Ive taken two of his classes so far, intro psych and stats. His stats was very very time consuming and extremely lecture and homework heavy. However, I still managed to finish with an A as hes super helpful and very clear in what he expects. He tends to take a while to answer emails but tends to be lenient and usually curves tests.

Very easy class, if you half attempt to do the work, you'll get an A. It's a hybrid class, so the lecture videos are online and followed by a quiz on Canvas. I never actually watched the lectures, just copied the notes and the quiz was easy. Discussion questions are hard and the reading are way too extensive.

The lecture is kinda boring but Dr.  does work hard to teach it. He covers tons of experiments and great ideas. This class also push me to read journals that I might have never read and I learn a lot from those. Tests are OPEN BOOK + 55 extra credits, so you can't complain for anything! Also, he is really patient and always ready to help.

Dr.  is a great professor, but definitely not a professor you want to take unless you are willing to put forth your best effort. She is extremely demanding, and expects 110% from her students. I learned a great deal from her class, and in the end, though I recived the lowest grade of my college career, I know I got the grade I earned.

She's a great teacher, and she made H101 extremely fun, interesting & relateable. She's a bit of a tough grader, but it's nothing unreasonable. I agree though, if you take H101, take it with her. And make sure you speak up. She likes people who talk a lot.
I really loved Stephane! Such a great guy and presents dull information in an interesting way. 2110 is really easy and he makes an effort to know all of his students.

Despite his accent he is able to communicate the material thoroughly, speaks better english than most native speakers. Learnt a great deal in his class as he encourages and spends time explaining things if you come halfway. Is very rigorous and knowledgeable but not inflexible, I have had him as an advisor so I know. I recomend meeting him halfway
Show up for in class assignments. He usually walks you through them for easy points
great guy, easy to understand his classes and very easy to get along.
Really interesting and funny guy. He's knowledgeable. Quizzes, tests, and discussion posts are all pretty easy, at least for the online version of this class.

is great, she spells out the expectations in the beginning, if you aren't up to it, drop. Class and lectures are enjoyable, be prepared to be challenged and actually learn something. Very aproachable, wants your patricipsation and feedback. As untraditional student, I find her class enjoyable! Notes are clear, tells you what to write down.

Professor  is a decent professor at OSU Mansfield. She remains unbiased in the politics class, even though her opinion on the matter is clear. She is easy to get along with, and is quite understanding when you must miss a class. However, some of her material is difficult to understand. I often found myself using Google to look up answers.

I took the Politics of the Developing World with Dr  and was not disappointed. He was committed to communicating the material well and I learned a lot. Lectures were sometimes dry, but if the course is interesting to you that's not going to be a big problem. Exams were straightforward and a list of essays were provided as a study guide

He doesn't take attendance, but it is impossible to do well without attending lecture. If you attend lecture, pay attention, take good notes, and study hard you can do well. This isn't an easy class and not really psychology. It's studying the advanced physiology and neuroscience of the human brain and neurological disorders. Loved it and the prof

Amazing is an understatement. She makes class enjoyable and makes you want to come to class. Exams are all written response but they were easier to me than my other classes as long as you study of course. She listens to her students and class is pretty straightforward. Theres easy extra credit. I took it with PSYCH3313 and it was a breeze.

The class was okay. Lectures not posted online, mostly studies and their results. Exams a lot harder than lecture, lots of material from the book. Not a lot of guidance for what to expect on the exam, but two small easy papers help your grade a little bit. Probably my least favorite class I took this quarter but it definitely could have been worse.
TAKE HIS CLASSES! He is the most wornderful professor I've found in the Poli Sci Department.

Dr  is the only reason I didn't drop out this semester. I didn't get to rate my professors on the SEIs because that week was very chaotic, but she deserves a raise. I know you read these, OSU. Get the Kowalskys out, and find more humans like this one. Her classes were fun, informative, and truly made me appreciate M&C. Thank you, Dr .

She is so fun and you can tell she genuinely cares about her class and students. She has tons of experience and stories and is very easygoing. She posts the learning objectives which follow the textbook, so studying for exams is very easy and she definitely isn't trying to trick you in the exams. Highly recommend taking her.

I took his online class and its the easiest A I've had so far at OSU. There was a lot of work, but he was a super lenient grader. The material was also really interesting. I would definitely take him again!

Interesting course. Lectures can be a bit boring but if you zone out/miss class you will miss ALOT. Tells you what will be on exam so you can prepare. Weird grading system where he adds up all points throughout the semester (only 3 exams worth 1/3 of grade) then gives out grades. No book, readings are all on Carmen.
She was so sweet and kind. Her lectures were posted on Camren to look back on, and everything tested was on the slides. There were no tricks in her class.

Dr.  was a great lecturer and is really passionate about Women's Gender Studies but oftentimes she would just lecture off tangent on things that we (the class) weren't sure of the relevance to the test. If you are passionate about Women's Studies this class will be easy but attendance is mandatory and the TAs are tough paper graders.

You have to keep up with either going to class or reading all the slides (which arent all the way filled out and you learn some terms in class only). It wasn't hard, per se. The lectures aren't all that exciting besides the biweekly activity. She is a good instructor, you just have to pay very close attention

The class is listed as a 3000 level course but could easily be a 4000 level course. He requires students to make a discussion post and take a quiz once a week and has 4 tests. Easily one of my least favorite professors
Awesome professor. Studied at some University called Cambridge? He adds like 20 points onto everyones quizzes and as long as you read the book theyre easy. If you like history then take this class

is a professor who truly cares about what he's teaching and teaching at large. He was very passionate in his lectures about every chapter we learned and was receptive to student comments. 2 mandatory exams and both were easy. Discussion posts were graded very leniently - just show effort and thinking. Weekly quizzes were easy.

This class is hard mostly because of all the information in the lectures. Studying is extremely difficult because he gives virtually no information about what is actually going to be on the exam so you end up spending a whole day going through hundreds of slides for a 32 question exam. He is very helpful answering questions during lectures tho
Very time consuming but assignments not graded to difficult.
Good lectures. Go to class in order to do well on the tests. Grades papers slightly hard. Knows his Ohio policitcs quite well.
A really great, interesting class.
I have taken one class with her psych 100 and I will not hesitate to take another with her, she is one of the best teachers I have had.
Really easy online class

Not sure why everyone thinks this class is so hard, maybe it depends on the T.A. Anyway, I highly recommend some kind of recording device for this class, as lectures consist entirely of him talking. Not the most enthralling class, but if you are pre-law I would seriously consider taking his section of this course. You will learn quite a lot.
Amazingly knowledgeable and informative. Notoriously difficult core class, wasnt so hard online and asynchronous but not sure if it asynchronous still
ok
Come to class and read the book and you will be good. His extra credit on the final was "Tell me a joke that has to do with statistics." Super helpful on homework and very approachable.

Dr.  is very clear in her lec. which are based on slides. Textb. difficult to get through; highly technical and dry. Exams mainly based off of lec. & slides. 4644 Hormones and Behavior has a lot of info. Dr.  seems to keep it on the simpler side, so if you are a neuroscience extraordinaire, it may not be detailed enough for your taste.
Very nice man, interesting class; genuinely decent human being and very bright man.

's a nice guy, and he grades quickly and very fairly. He's got a good sense of humor and responds to emails incredibly fast. While his rubrics and tests are clear, he doesn't describe assignments well. Very repetitive, mind-numbing lecture. It's offputting that the course totally revolves around his research, but not a bad option overall.

Not worth it to take as a 100 level teacher. Enthusiastic about material, not in making work load appropriate for a 100 level class. Too much outside reading required, mandatory attendance in lecture and recitation, 5 papers plus final and midterm. Material v. interesting, it just took way too much work to get an A.

Professor  is one of the best instructors I have had so far throughout my college career. He is a very tough grader but it made me think significantly more about the content of the class, as opposed to someone who just gave completion credit or graded with minimal effort. He obviously cares about his students' lives in and out of the classroom.
Tests are confusing but was an interesting class and he is a nice guy.
Excellent teacher, brilliant person. he expects a lot but he is very helpful to anyone who really wants to learn

Very enthusiastic and never stops moving. He's definitely smart, but too smart for his own good. He sees all sorts of connections between concepts but struggles to explain it to students. He tries to explain things but can't maintain a clear train of thought. Always late to class, but he tries to help outside of class if you can reach him.

Dr.  is amazing in his field, but he expects you to share in his passion. It took me a while to realize this, but the tests are largely based off of class notes, but you can't get them unless you show up to every class. I struggled, but I was always below the average, so it might have just been me.
He is great. You do a lot of reading but then go over it in class. Hes very engaging and does a lot of funny things to keep it interesting. Great guy.

Professor  is awesome! He doesn't want to tank your GPA or make your life difficult for no reason. The entire class is graded by your midterm and final. He gives you plenty of resources on Carmen (including past tests ;) ) I 100% recommend taking this class.
Dr.  made this class much better than I expected! Go to class and ask questions when they come up!
This is literally the easiest class ever.  even tells you how to correct your papers for a better grade if you need to improve your scores.

not a very tough class. lectures can be a bit tough to stay awake through, but as long as you have an idea of the readings and go over class notes really well before tests its not bad. simple participation ups your grade too...easy

The class was pretty easy. She read everything straight from the slides, which were available online so basically I hardly ever went to class. She does offer extra credit points from time to time for attendance, needless to say I didnt get any but I did recieve an A- in the class anyway. Read the notes and read your book, you'll be A OK

Dr.  is an amazing professor and extremely caring! The only bad part of his class was the harsh attendance policy - no makeups, even if you were sick and have a doctor's note. He was a thoroughly engaging professor with a strong passion for sociology.

Didn't do well in the last 2 exams but still got an A.. due to the awesome extra credit. She might not have tons of jokes to entertain you, but if you really listen, the class is actually interesting. she is very nice and helpful too. the exam are not super easy, but read the slides, you will be fine.

He is really intelligent and makes class interesting. There was a data project about one of several topics relating to the presidency: mine was about the relationship between the state of the economy and the probability for an incumbent to be re-elected. It is a really fun project, and you should get an A if you take it seriously.

Professor  is extremely nice and knows what she is talking about. Her class focuses on democracy and she does a great job teaching it. I don't think its necessary to read the textbook if you take god notes but MAKE SURE TO DO THE READINGS. There are a few quizzes, decently hard midterm essay, and a take home final.

Absolutely loved this class and this man! It was so interesting and he's incredibly smart. You should really go to class and if you get into the assignments, you can come out of the class with vast knowledge on the subject matter. I would even take it again someday (and might audit it..). Definitely take it if you like international relations!

Class discussions are very fun/interesting and you learn a lot during them. Lecture style can get boring. The only thing that bothered me is that he didn't seem organized. He took a long time to get things up on carmen and then he didn't even pass back our exams so we could see what we got wrong. Nevertheless, he's a great guy and a decent prof.

Not many points available, only 200 for the whole Social Psych class, yet a tough grader and she even said "you won't get 100% on some papers". No extra credit available. I found myself struggling to get every point I could.
Class is almost interesting, completely lecture. He assigns two books, but only uses the reader. He is a smart guy and understand the subject well. Take the full essay format exams- way easier

Took this class during Covid-19 times and you REALLY have to work hard for a good grade. There are at least 2 short papers each week, which she expects you to discuss during Zoom meetings. She doesn't give rubrics, just gives examples of previous student papers. You can only miss like 2 classes without tanking your participation grade.

The class and material were interesting, but I found that his lectures could get really tedious, and his exams were extremely difficult. He words things in a confusing way, and I often found things on the tests that were not discussed in the book or in lecture.
Dr.  is a fun understanding professor. Just be upfront with what is going on in your life and he will work around you. Showing up for class is 50% of your grade, so make sure to go.

Great Professor. He genuinely cares about the class and the topics. You just have to read some online articles and write a page summary, one movie group project, and the 2 midterms (which were not hard). You can miss 4 classes but if you know you will miss more it will drop you 10% from your final grade automatically.

He is funny and his lectures were pretty entertaining but sometimes no matter how hard I tried I still had trouble understanding what we were talking about. I think political theory might just be a difficult subject in general. I wish he would have been more clear with what we were supposed to take away from each reading.

This class is NOT difficult. The tests are a bit hard but the curve is huge and if you pay attention, do the reading, and study you should do fine on them without the curve anyway. This class is definitely worth your time.
is an expert on Congress and highly recommended. Personable, entertaining class, and genuinely cares about his students
is a great professor who is passionate about global politics. Buying the book is necessary, although you do not have to read 100% of it--but very helpful to read in preparation for an exam.

Dr.  was a kind man, however, it can be difficult to be engaged in his lectures. I almost never attended his class meetings on Zoom and I got a good grade. He only rounds up by half percentages, so I could not convince him to round a 92 to an A.

I really enjoyed her class, but I will say that if you're planning on skipping a lot (like me), you will lose quite a few participation points. There were weekly journal articles, but they weren't super hard and didn't take a lot of time. Class discussions were always interesting and she definitely makes it an open space for lots of opinions.
Pretty chill teacher overall. Watch the lectures and read the textbook and you'll pass just fine.

this class was super interesting and I really enjoyed it! Easy A if you do the work!!! I would say I spent an average of 30 min per week on this class and got an A. The actual class sessions are super easy and lowkey.  is very kind and understanding and knowledgeable in his field. Guest lectures are usually very good as well. Class can be long

This was my favorite course as a SOC major. Her lectures are organized, easy to follow, and she makes great use of multimedia and visual aids. You can get by on the exams without doing the reading...however the reading material is actually pretty interesting and dare I say...enjoyable. TAKE THIS COURSE!

was the most caring professor I've ever met! He genuinely cares about all his students and will go out of his way to help you succeed. His lectures are fun and engaging and he thoroughly explains any questions we have. With that being said his exams are a but difficult because you have to remember many equations and understand all material.

Dr. MacGilvray is amazing, but the class is definitely hard. It's totally worth it, but you have to study, and take really detailed notes during class (look out for buzz words!). His class consists of three exams, each worth 30% of your grade, and 5 pop quizzes (lowest one dropped), for the remaining 10%. He's really funny and intelligent.

I think there are so many negative responses just because the midterm and final ask some very specific questions about the readings and lectures rather than "big picture" stuff, but people don't like to pay attention or read much for gen eds. All the assignments (including the one essay) are graded very easily and aren't difficult.
Grade is mainly test based and communication outside of classroom is not that great.
Dr.  is an amazing professor and i strongly recommend taking him! He makes class really interesting and is very funny! take him!
The lectures were pretty boring for me, but Dr.  does everything she can to make class more fun. She is very kind and helpful.
He had a great sense of humor and had great class discussions.

Had him for 501 and H613. Very hard courses, but if you are good at integrating information, getting the "big picture" and knowing the details he emphasizes, you can pull off an A. It takes a lot of effort though. TONS of reading for 613. I recommend him, even if it slashes your GPA!
Nice guy, lectures were interesting. Reading the textbook is important and theres a lot of it
You do need to go to lecture and take notes, but the class is very interesting and not too hard. Prof Reczek is nice and pretty personable.

She's pleasant and cares about her students. Has a quiz every week on the long readings, and these affect your grade. Don't skip. Allows one OOPS pass that allows you to drop your lowest grade. Beyond this, she's inflexible; no extra credit with her. Doesn't upload class slides online. TAKE NOTES! Allows one page of notes (double-sided) for exams.

Dr.  assigned almost 50 pages a class, and we had a class quiz every class and an outside quiz after every class. Exams were not that hard if you came to class & paid attention, but it was just A LOT of reading & work. He expects you to memorize charts & schematics (of memory paths, for example) I'm not a math guy, so the cog. part was hard.

cares about his students and knows what hes talking about. He listens to feedback from the students to help us out. He gave us 3 extra points from unfair test questions, as well as 5 easy points EC (if one other person in your group did it, he gave it to all of you). Not mandatory, but going to class is needed to get in class activity points.

was a professor that cared A LOT about what she taught, as well as having a good relationship with her students. This class style is different than others in the way that there were no exams, almost all of the points came from in-class participation and assignments. Its a good filler class, but there is work during class unlike others.
You do need to go to lecture and take notes, but the class is very interesting and not too hard. Prof  is nice and pretty personable.

Good professor, easy class. Don't need to read textbook, tests are easy. She records the lectures, but I'm not sure if that's because of COVID. Would probably be boring if I had to go to class because it takes me 15 minutes to watch each lecture once I skip past everything irrelevant and play it at double speed. She's caring and easygoing.

In all honesty, the content for this class can be boring especially in an 1 hour 20 minute lecture. But I must say, Dr.  took the time to help me not only with coursework but with life issues. She cares about her students and her role at Ohio State. I will forever be thankful for Dr.  and recommend her if you have the option.

decent professor and a funny guy, although you don't really learn a lot in his class. exams are not fun at all, since he doesn't provide an outline of terms or anything to that extent in the way of preperation. overall it's not that difficult of a class, just be prepared to spend time working outside of class doing volunteering, surveys, etc.

She really cares that her students do well in the class and gives many opportunities to bring up your grade. Participation matters but she gives more than enough opportunities to earn all the points. She usually tries to end class early, and reviews after every section. She drops 6/11 quizzes and 2/3 written assignments. I would take it again

Dr.  is not the professor you want to take for an easy A, but if you genuinely want to learn, she is perfect. Her lectures were never boring. This class is a lot of work and I would not recommend going in expecting an A because you'll likely be disappointed, but the amount I learned from this class made it so worth it!

Dr.  is great. This was by far one of my favorite Neuro courses. Would leave class everyday fascinated. Drops lowest Midterm grade but ended up allowing us to drop our cumulative final because the averages were low. Super fair and great!

professor  is soo funny and makes sure that he is available for students whenever they need. it's very clear that he genuinely cares about teaching and his students. the course load is heavy and confusing at times but very interesting. if you're confused about something, he provides great explanations and will clear things up. def recommend

I love his class. He's funny and very enthusiastic about the subject matter, which makes it much more interesting. Grade is based entirely on 2 tests, but his grading is flexible. Also, he has a fun English accent. Overall, great professor! Take his class!

Dr  is my absolute favorite professor of all time. I already took her classes and specifically signed up for another one because of how much I enjoyed her teaching style. Dr.  was great. This class was my second time having him and while he is a little monotoned, his lectures show that he a professional in his field. Very inspired by her work. She is always excited and ready to talk about politics. As someone who isnt interested in politics, i was made a little interested because of this professor

I love her!! She is the best prof. ever!!! I wish I could take all of her classes! I love the way she explains and talks in her lectures! Even just the class topics are very interesting.

is a very good professor and really cares about what he does. Dr.  is the best!

Professor MacEachern knows his stuff and more importantly he cares about his students. I felt he was very available. He can be disorganized - it is especially challenging when there is no textbook to fall back on.

If you come to class and listen you will be fine. Tests are completely fair. She seemed to be that professor that wanted to be more reasonable Bc she knows we have other classes and that made me appreciative.

Professor  was amazing! She's an attorney, so she's very knowledgeable about the subject matter and it shows how much she cares about it. one of the easiest classes ive ever taken . Professor  was super understanding and sweet gave extensions on assignments. Easy class does require a textbook as long as you read the textbooks youll do fine in the class

Professor  is a good guy. His class is easy, but you learn a lot. I thought the material was interesting - and you could see that he enjoyed teaching it.

is a great guy, he went out of his way to help me find an article that I needed for my research paper.

Such an amazing professor! Class is okay just as long as you read the textbook, study, and pay attention to the lectures. You can tell he loves what he does and wants all his students to succeed. Btw he is absolutely hilarious. Definetly recommend taking his class!

Professor  is a really kind Professor and is genuinely passionate about her teachings. I didnt think the homework was too overbearing and the quizzes were pretty easy. Towards the end of the semester some of the classes got a little boring, but the material was presented well.

Dr.  is such a wonderful person. I genuinely felt bad for skipping her lectures so often because she is such a kind-hearted soul. She is a very easy grader, if you come to the lectures you don't really need to do the readings. She friendly and enthusiastic, defiantly an expert in her field. I would take her again.

Course material is difficult, but he makes it understandable and interesting. Very helpful. Liberal grader and very fair. Big paper, but you pick the topic. Definitely would take him again...brilliant.

Dr.  is just lovely! Her lectures were as entertaining as they were informative and she's super approachable and kind. dr.  was teriffic. he has an amazing amount of knowledge and experience in this subject. he communicate very well and teaches in an exciting manner. he makes sure that everyone can understand and master the materail. i would recommend taking a c

This is the BEST class and prof I have ever had. He is a renowned Political Scientist and it is easy to see why after taking his class. He is organized, intelligent and straight-forward. This class is a must-take, especially if you are poli sci at OSU!

For being a three credit hour course, he takes it a little too far. Nobody had any idea what would actually be on exam and exam questions were not clearly mentioned on study guide. It was kind of a hopefully I retained this information that he said once during this lecture type deal.
Professor  is a great professor. He is super chill if you get to know him. The labs are pretty quick. Exams are not too difficult. Engage in the class and you'll do well.
pretty good class. as long as you study well you should do fine. very clear in her teaching and standards.
Never read textbook or went to class. Lectures good, homework kind of busywork, but easy points. Interesting topics, easy tests, would take again.

she is great!!you do not have to be good in math to do well in her class! she gives alot of examples so that you understand. 4 assignments through out the quarter which was not bad and a midterm and a final. TAs were really helpful also!

Amazing prof and engaging/ hilarious lectures.  readings (40-80+ pgs) that go with 12 quizzes that make up the majority of your grade. Take this class immediately if you are looking for easy GE. You do not have to study for a thing and literally can get an A by spending 15 min a week on it (taking the quiz). Its all online.

Very nice man- let me add the course in the 3rd week with no problem. Very friendly. Can be a bit boring in lecture, tends to ramble on. Likes the subject a lot. Exams are a bit lengthy, but just know your stuff and you will do fine. Lecture attendance is mandatory, he goes over what he wants you to know for exams. TAKE THIS CLASS!

She is a great professor; gives extremely good feedback. If you work for it, you can easily get an A

Dr.  definitely knows how to hold your attention at 8:00 am, he's definitely a teacher worth studying under. Keep up with readings, pay attention to key details and know your concepts. With a moderate amount of studying, this class isn't a tough A.

Incredibly smart and educated professor. Great class. Lots of information in a short amount of time. Very quiet speaker but values opinions and discussion. Not an easy A but you will get a lot out of this class if you put the effort in.
the comment from 4/27/2015 is 100% correct. if you do well on the quizzes and by well i mean above (75%) and do all the participation quizzes you should be able to get an A.
Dr.  is the Best. Recommend his American Presidency class!
I didn't watch any of the lectures. I did 20% of the additional readings and did not read the textbook once. I got an A.

Professor  is a very swell guy. I would say lectures are mandatory if you want to have success in this class, especially if you do not have a background in data. is literally amazing! She is such a sweetheart and taught a difficult class with grace, kindness, and openness. She does everything in her power to make the class stimulating, but it is on the lecture heavy side. I can't wait to take another class with her!

Dr.  was awesome. This class was about psychology podcasts and was mainly a discussion-based class. She was very interesting and intelligent and it was a very engaging class that felt like a community. It's very easy to get an A as long as you show up every day and do the discussion posts.
Fantastic lectures filled with debates over cases and decisions surrounding law. He is a great guy. Would recommend if you are at all interested in law and or an easy A.
You need to watch the lecture videos for points, but the exams are completely open: youre even allowed to use Google. As long as you put in minimal effort, its easy to get an A.

She is an amazing teacher. Come prepared to talk about material in class. She doesn't like to just lecture at you so be involved. Read the material and come to class. Hello this is college do the work. She is completely awesome.
Tough class and confusion around some expectations but with effort I did learn a lot.

I would highly recommend this course for those interested in sociology or who see themselves furthering their education in the subject. For people like myself, who are just trying to fulfill a course requirement this professor is not for that. This course is lecture heavy. FYI: 10 points are taken from your following exam per class missed.

Showing up for class isn't mandatory, but its a good idea; he goes over a lot of stuff in class and makes things a lot easier to understand. Exams are important, so STUDY, but he's pretty generous about curves.
so nice, will always go out of his way to help students. class was not too hard, and he even though it was stats, he sometimes made it interesting
Dr  is the best instructor/professor I have ever had in my whole life. He inspires me to be better. His examples help make learning easy and fun. Please take his classes and you won't regret it.

Dr.  was awesome! This class was defiantly a class that people wanted to go to, because everything we talked about could be related back to our own lives. Overall a great class, and I would recommend this class even if you are not a psych major, because you learn so much useful information.

I learned so much from  in my gender class. For one, she didn't teach a regular lecture(slide)class. The students were communicating with each other, and the conversations had a lasting impression on me. I find myself talking about the content of the course to everyone I encounter now. Thank you for this delightful experience, .

Pop quizzes over readings. Only two other grades, a midterm and a final where you just write everything you can possibly remember. Review sessions are a must.

did a very good job teaching the course. He is very smart and this showed in his lectures. Dr.  is very passionate about legislative politics. The class is easy, though there are quite a few books (a fair amount for a 500 level class). Responds to emails very fast and is a nice person.

While learning the content was interesting, when it came to the exams he was a tough grader. He really expects you to make them quality essays, so it wasn't as easy as I expected.

Dr.  is very passionate about what he teaches, so even though it can be very boring, he does his best to make it interesting. There were 12 quizzes, 4 exams, a very strict no technology policy, and attendance is mandatory. He sets very clear expectations for the class which is nice. If you put in the work/pay attention, then you should be ok.

I loved having Dr. ! He was super interested in the subject material and made a long lecture fun with his humor. Tests are super fair, he gives a study guide and as long as you understand the material, you should have no problem doing well. With a slight curve, I got above 100 on one of his midterms. He's a really nice guy, too.
Dr.  is awesome! She is such a positive beginning to my mornings and her lectures are great! The TAs on the other hand...
Good teacher. Easy class, didn't use the book at all, but really good information.

I looked forward to this class; it is interesting, informative, and unique. Dr.  knows her stuff and has fun teaching it. She is a great professor to get to know: down-to-earth, friendly, and passionate. A fun class that is not too difficult but not too easy either. If you interested, psych major or not, take this class.

Dr.  is absolutely wonderful. He is entertaining, interesting, and always open to discussion. He will answer any questions for you after class and he posts all of his powerpoints online. Although he does not take attendance, I would highly recommend attending his lectures. And reading the book is a must! Take his class if you can.

This is a very writing and reading heavy course. There are required readings weekly and each reading is around 15-25 pages long. Plus textbook reading and smaller readings. If I would have known this was a reading and writing course, I wouldn't have taken the class.
very nice and interesting! Explains everything clearly

Dr.  is an excellent professor. He seems to genuinely enjoy teaching. His lectures are interesting. I would absolutely take him again. The tests are taken directly from the lecture notes. He is very passionate about the material and tries to get everyone interested. His expectations are clear.

Dr.  is funny and just a very welcoming person in general. I was never scared to ask him a question! His quizzes and exams were very fair, and he graded papers very leniently too. I was not a big fan of the weekly breakout room session, but I understand why he did them.

Exams are fair and pretty easy if you study the slides well and pay attention to videos she shows in class. Your grade is basically based on the best out of three of exams so you have the option to not take the exam. Great class. For neuro majors this is basically a review of everything you've ever learned from other classes.
this dude is the only teacher that can hold my attention at 8 in the morning. we get alot done in class and he makes it interesting. greatest teacher i've ever had in my life.

Professor 's class isn't "easy" but you will learn a lot. I truly feel lucky to have been able to take 2 classes with him. You won't meet a professor at OSU that's more knowledgeable, kind, and caring. And he's hilarious.

Professor  was super helpful and super clear. He wants his students to succeed and it's very easy to get a good grade in the class. He gives out a study guide before the test that tells you exactly what the test is on so if you get a bad grade, it's your own fault. Sometimes there is random participation points.
Great prof. Gives test questions beforehand, and a country memo essay at the end. Attendance isn't taken either. Great guy too and is funny.

Dr.  is very intelligent and such a sweet person. I loved going to his class simply because he was funny and was great at what he does. The material to me was very hard... he speaks quickly and seems to forget we don't have a graduate degree and are as talented as himself. But he will go above and beyond for his students if needed.
Dr.  is a fun guy. He gets the point across and does so in an interesting manner.

The books and material are challenging, but his lectures are great and he gives you lots of ways to absorb the material (lecture, section, online lecture slides). Really not a hard class if you do the reading.

Obviously knows his stuff, he literally "wrote the book" on developmental morality. Great genuine guy and solid professor

Very interesting class, but it's a long lecture so it is difficult to sit through. A lot of people had trouble with the tests for some reason, but I thought they were fair and I found that reading trough lecture slides was sufficient to study from and I got an A on all three tests. I didn't need the book at all.
The exams are hard and all essay questions. But he is very helpful.
Really easy and interesting class. One of the easiest honors classes to take, as long as you can keep up with the reading, you should do fine.
Easy class IF you go to lecture. The only grades are the midterms and two in class essays, though. There's a lot of extra credit, but you really have to work for it.

The material itself is great! He presents the material in an entertaining way. The tests are really hard even if you read the book. I ended up with a B and went to class every day and asked questions. Still I would recommend this class!

She is a tough grader, but she intends well. She wants to make sure youre prepared and that you know your material. The book for the class is arduous, but her lectures really help concepts come to life and the homeworks help make those concepts more concrete. I would highly recommend her!
Pretty good!Highly recommended!
Genuinely interested in teaching. A lot of class discussion; really made the class more about the students and less about himself.
Had him for psych 1100; a great choice for my first college class. Thought it was pretty easy. He curved most our tests 6-10 points. Was very happy with the overall experience.

Professor  was amazing. If you are seriously considering law school, I definitely recommend taking one of his classes. I learned more in this class than I learned in any other political science classes combined.
Great professor, got me interested in this topic and now I'm going to graduate school!
She is very nice and very smart. She is very involved and interested in teaching her subject. She makes it hard to participate in class discussions, but overall the class was great.

Dr.  is very invested in your success. He could be driving, eating, or sleeping but he will still take the time to answer your question. It is an easy A if you follow his instructions which are clear. The course is also very organized.

I really enjoyed 's class. Some of his exams questions are tricky but if you study the study guide he gives and pay attention in class, you should be fine. Lots of discussion during his lectures which was nice. I learned a lot in this class.
I've taken a lot of Psych classes with Dr  because he is one of the best instructors. He is really helpful and makes things relate to you. He's really interesting and genuinely enjoys teaching.

He's a really nice guy. Really cares about what he is teaching and is always willing to help. I've grown to like Dr.  and am going to miss him after this semester. I'm not sure why people are so hard on him.

If you have a chance to take a class with Dr. . Do it. He is incredibly kind and cares so much for his students. Any and all of your questions will be answered in depth and he is very accommodating. The content can be a lot but if you follow the syllabus, you'll be fine

It was a pretty standard sociology class. He did a good job and really tried to get the class to debate the readings. (He did a pretty good job considering our class was at 8:00am). She is extremely knowledgable and loves what she teaches. Class can get boring at times and she may not be as engaging but she cares about the subject a lot. Absolutely loved   as a professor. Literally, the best professor I've ever had hands down. His exams can be vigorous but his class is an absolute must-take, a professor I will never forget.

This course is super simple. If you have a basic understanding of the US legal system this should be a breeze. Just weekly assignments, three exams, and one 4-6 page paper. If you just complete all the work you should get an A.

This guy really knows his stuff. He is incredibly knowledgeable in his field. The problem comes in his tests; they are really hard and incorporate very little from class. I loved this class. Dr.  made things easy to understand and was overall a very great guy. Take this class if you get a chance!

Aces clearly loves the information he is teaching, the class had only three test- which he curved and extra credit was able to be given. There was a textbook- but I never bought it. I put this class on the back burner of 18 credit hours- not that it is easy, just never any commitment besides the three exams.

Honestly a really nice guy. His class was completely asynchronous and every week there is a quiz and application. Overall, good class just watch and study the content. Also give grace periods!

is great, she makes the class material fun and tells you exactly what you will need to do in order to do well in the class. You have to go to lectures since the notes are not filled out online and she takes attendance, but they are a great time and even more fun if you participate.

Professor Harvey was really nice and the class was fairly easy. There was no final exam, just a final paper and a presentation that had to be done. Both were pretty easy. This was his first semester teaching this class so it was kinda disorganized, but still very easy A. He had all the exams take home, open note, online so that was nice. Honestly learned more from the book than class, but he does easy reading quizzes every class so you have to show up.

Super funny and clearly loves sociology. His lectures are funny, most content id from textbook.1-2 chapters per week, a lecture video, and a discussion post. She is a very nice professor and gives out lots of extra credit. Sometimes a fast talker but overall helpful.

I really like her. I think she is tough, but very fair! She makes you think and work for your grade. I found the class to be very interesting. Not a slack off class. I found her to be very helpful answering questions. I would take another of her classes.

was a great professor! I felt that she genuinely had a passion for her subject. She doesn't round up/give extra credit, which isn't an issue for many but for some it could be. Roughly 80 pages of reading a week. Pop quizzes throughout. Three exams. First exam had an in-class and out of class portion. In-class was a long-form essay. Out of class was a four page paper. Dr.  is a wonderful professor. No political science degree is complete without taking his classes. Lectures were interesting, and I learned a great deal from him.

Professor  is awesome! She is so interactive and makes it a goal to know everyone on a personal level. I loved her class and it was super interesting to take during the corona crisis. I highly recommend her, her exams are easy, her lectures are straight forward and she is awesome!

Professor  is very nice and I found the class decently interesting just very repetitive. The review lectures prep you for quizzes and tests very well. Very organized in the online format and very little work to do. Just 5 quizzes and 2 tests are graded.

Very good teacher! My favorite psych class I've taken for the past 4 years. The only hard part is that there is a big paper at the end and a cumulative final, but there are many small assigments along the way for the paper so you can't get behind.
Great Professor!!!

There was a lot of reading but it was not necessary. Could retake most quizzes an unlimited number of times. Directions for papers were sometimes unclear, but she was very good at responding to emails in a timely manner and answered questions well. She is a very easy grader.

He is super easy. You just have some quizzes which he sends the questions out a day early so you just show up and fill it out. He has required workshops but doesn't take attendance (but can be fun). Midterm and final are easy. Basically just a pretty easy class where you learn some useful things.
She really enjoys what she teaches helping interest you in the material.

He is a good professor. His exams are not too difficult and he does curve them to an extent. He is passionate about what he is teaching and wants his students to do well. Also, don't get too scared of the 8-10 page paper he has you write. It's not that bad. The lectures are somewhat interesting, but can make you sleepy at times. Overall, decent!

Prof  is a lighthearted, happy guy. He is a brilliant man and genuinely interested in his work. He is always glad to help students and is very approachable. He explains topics pretty well. The readings are tough but his lectures are where you learn the most. Pop quizzes were pretty hard, and the partial open note tests were decently hard

Attendance is semi-mandatory. He grades toughly but is clear is what his expectations are. Reading quizzes are easy and a good way to pad out your grade. Interesting lectures and clearly knows what he is talking about. Readings are not overwhelming.

Good professor. Does not post notes on Carmen, must attend class for notes. Two easy papers to write, 3 pages at most. Studying is required, but it isn't hard material. Mostly common sense. I recommend  if you want an easy A.

He makes class pretty interesting. You don't need to attend because basically the same stuff is in the text book, but he makes it so easy to understand. He's very organized so taking notes is easy. Tests are simple as long as you reread notes and text.

This class is easy and there are no exams or quizzes. You basically work on a semester long project with your group every week. There are homework assignments and journals. The assignments are very easy they both took me no longer than an hour at best. Everyone ends up with an A. I ended with a 99% A.

This class was a great course for getting feet wet into classes at OSU. In my personal opinion, this asynchronous course allowed plenty of time to finish coursework throughout the entire semester. Professor  was amazing in how much extra credit that you received during the semester. The textbook is an easy read, the assignments are easy.

He is a great teacher and you will learn a lot. However, it is an EXTREMELY difficult class. I took it while taking 24 credit hours and I simply didn't have the time to do well in the course. Only take it if you have LOTS of time to dedicate to the class. Also, he doesn't require attendance, but you have to go to pass.
Great guy. Very clear and easy to understand.
Gives great feedback and clearly outlines what she's looking for in her assignments. In class, she's able to moderate debate while not showing much bias toward either side.
I took psych 3325 and she was amazing. Group assignment and homework/quizzes.

Super informative. Well spoken, easy to follow. Some complex material at times. Lectures are overall interesting and he keeps your attention (if you care at all about the subject matter). Your grade comes from midterms and exam which are all long answeressay but he tells you what to know and provides study guides!!! Most should get an A or B here!

This class at its roots is easy. There are no exams and your grade is based mainly around a semester-long group video project. The topics are interesting and Dr.  is very passionate about his field. However, the class is not organized well and is heavy in "busy work".
The best professor I've ever had. Informative lectures, quick responses, and clear explanations. Take him if you want to pass the course and truly learn something.

is so sweet and caring. She reminds me of my own grandmother. The class is very straightforward and easy to do well in as long as you do the weekly assignments (some of which are worth as much as your final exam). The content is very interesting, but most of the time I learned it all myself before the two exams. No class on Friday.

Tis class had so many components to it. Dr.  made assignments harder than they needed to be and she graded just as harder or even harder. We had a huge group project and our honestly did really well but she graded us harshly and a lot of people's grades drop at the end. The public health classes are easy but this one was hard for no reason.

She gets really excited when she talks, she is great about engaging students and having discussions while staying on topic, even with 60 students. She moved back due dates a lot, which was helpful. It was great that she let us choose whether we wanted to take an exam or write a paper. We could get away with not doing all the readings.
Doesn't respond to emails. Exams are hard and take all day to complete.

Dean  is a good teacher. He is very informative and does a great job relating the topics to more recent elections. The class can get boring at times, but it is very interesting. The class is not too difficult and the paper topic is very interesting.

He has passages that should be read prior to each class and I did not read one of them. He goes over them in depth in class and that was enough for me to do very well on the written portion of the exam. The class is hard but there was a google doc full of notes that was helpful for studying. It's an interesting class and his Qs are conceptual.

Jeff is a nice and easygoing professor and gives interesting lectures. Class grade is made up of 4 exams, 3 papers, and 10 weekly discussion posts. Papers are gradely leniently but you need to study for the exams. Use the study guide he gives! Overall an ok class and not a hard A.

I love ! She is a great professor and you can tell she loves what she is doing. You must attend her classes to pass because there is in class work. Her class is very interesting and I highly recommend taking any of her classes! She is great!
Dr.  is awesome. Her class is super informative, and she's great at teaching the material. If you do the work, you'll get the grade you want.

A good prof and clearly very passionate about the subject. You're graded on 3 midterms and a final, you can drop one of the midterms but you have to take the final. She also gives a study guide for exams which other Neuro profs don't. Definitely recommend

Readings could be long, but were interesting. Reading quizzes were not overly difficult. Lectures were solid and slideshow heavy, still interesting though. Encouraged participation. Final paper was very long/tough but very fairly graded with good feedback. Midterm and Final were good. Only take the class if you truly care about the content.

Very friendly and easy to contact. His job and his students are his #1 priority. He made video lectures for his online students and gave us tons of helpful resources to study. Without discipline to study, the class can be hard because there is a lot of information. Be warned that you need extra time out of class to do the REP credits.

It's hard to fully judge him based off the circumstances with switching to online classes, but this class was really interesting and I learned a lot. It required a lot of reading with daily reading quizzes, but it is very heavily curved to make up for the difficulty. I recommend it to anyone interested, but definitely requires some effort!

He was helpful if you went to office hours. There was no book required for the class. The exams were partially open note. Almost every class, he does not tell you what he wants you to know. He just lets the conversation go where it may. Some of the really difficult readings you may not pick up on the main points unless he gives you a pop quiz.

knows what he is talking about. You will learn a lot in his course, but you have to pay attention. Attendance isn't recorded, but it's a lot easier to understand the material if you're present. Only had four grades the whole semester (four tests). He answers any questions and is always available. I recommend the professor and the course.
Dr.  is one of the best professors at OSU. Very knowledgable and funny during his lectures. Exams are tough but fair because he usually curves them.

Not a very engaging professor, but the class is easy. Powerpoints are straight from the book and tests are straight froom the powerpoints..do not buy book! You can find it at the library reserves. Only 3 tests, with the lowest dropped. Grades are curved at the end..interesting material!

My favorite class I've ever taken was the one I took with him. He doesn't take attendance (though he notices those who show up) but GO TO CLASS. He's a great lecturer and if you know your lectures and cases you'll be fine . Sit towards the front to be one of Larry's favorites. You'll just want him to like you. It'll just make you feel good.

Really engaging, and in a class that's centered around the President, he makes a concious effort to stay as nonpartisan and unbiased as possible. He is extremely engaging, and present his leftures in a way that makes you think. My favorote class I've taken so far, and one of the most fair classes I've taken. 10/10 would reccomend this professor.

Online lectures were the only thing that you needed to take notes on, because the class lectures were a repeat of the online ones. She assigns a TON of reading that is graded extremely tough by her TAs. The tests are easy and they are mostly made of quiz and discussion questions so as long as you study a little and do the homework, you are fine.

Dr.  is very knowledgable and down-to-earth with his students. Lecture is pretty important, as he explains a lot that aren't in his slides.
