There's also just a lot of material covered in this class, so going to lecture helps.

I literally switched my major to public health after this class. I would say that the time in class is not productive, and most of the homework out of class takes some time to do (1 page writing and 1 easy quiz a week for the most part), but the content is very interesting. We read novels relating to public health. Loved this class and professor

She is so amazing!! I love this woman. She is so smart and helpful, and is so great to just talk to about life. She is so clear in lectures and very engaging. I used the textbook in this class purely as a study aid for when I had to miss class-- attend lectures and office hours and you will get an A!
One of the very few professors that want you to actually learn the information. She does not rely on tests to check your knowledge. Had great humor and was very caring.

Dr.  is a good professor and is very willing to help students. His only downfall is that he has a tendency to lecture directly from his powerpoint slides. This class is not hard, if you find PS4315 difficult and are studying polysci int studies you should probably change your major.

Dr.  is a really great teacher! I feel like I learn a lot from her, and she is challenging in a good way. I took Behavioral Neuro with her and am now taking Hormones and Behavior and I love both classes.
Class material is very easy and obvious. A bit picky about grading on tests, but overall an easy course without much work.
Simply awesome - best professor I ever had.

I LOVE Dr. . She's very relaxed about teaching and just wants her students to understand more about hormones and the brain. There are 4 multiple choice exams and 10 points of extra credit given throughout the course. One exam is dropped from your grade, but you have to take the final. She can be so funny during lecture too in very subtle ways

This was absolutely my favorite class taken @ OSU so far. She knows her stuff and I learned SO much from this class. I forgot to fill out my student evaluation for her, so I'm giving her an A+ on her

Professor  was one of my favorite professors that I have ever had. He is very entertaining, and makes the topic more interesting than it actually is. He is a fair grader, but you do definitely have to work for a good grade. He is not intimidating and always there to help. Definitely take his class if you get a chance!
He is an amazing professor. He gives lots of extra credit. Would recommend.

This class was the hardest class I took this semester but also my favorite. Dr.  is genuinely passionate about the subject and very knowledgeable, he's also pretty funny and manages to make even the most boring topics interesting to learn about. It is a lot of reading/taking notes but if you keep up with it it's not too bad! I'd recommend it.

You will do very well if you study. Grades are determined by the tests. All the material is based off of the power points and what he says. Going to office hours will help because he repeats content from lecture then.

Lectures not mandatory. If you read the books you don't need to go. Such a nice and brilliant man. Long paper assigned, and is expected to be heavy in statistical data. Even if you go to lecture, buy the book. It's very hard to take notes and stay focused. Great man

's class was a real joy to take. Though heavy on in-depth readings each week with corresponding discussion questions, a couple of those grades are dropped so you can catch a few breaks. Definitely challenging and interesting to anybody interested in sociology. TA's helpful. Exams require very little study if you've been paying attention.

Dr.  gives out extra credit like candy on Halloween. This semester, he gave out 70 points of extra credit out of 500 total points, so if you get all of the EC and try in the class, you are well underway for an A in the class.

Professor  is the best in the field for a reason. His lectures are incredible and he really makes you think through the material. Easily approachable and very friendly, definitely not a stuffy suit political scientist. One of the nicest people I have had the pleasure of being taught by. Alex is brilliant and his work is amazing.

Prof  was one of the nicest professors I've had. Really into psych and makes the class easy to understand. As long as you do the study guides, you're bound to ace the class. After unfortunately mixing up exam dates, I recieved a very low grade for one of the exams. I explained the sitaution and he dropped the exam from my overall grade. Amazing

I enjoyed this class. He posts slides on carmen, but does add more informations during lecture. While lecture is not mandatory, I would recommend attending for the extra information. He has lots of stories that relates with the material. The test are from both lecture and books. It's not a bad class to take and has a nice curve.

She was alright. She gives you the whole test to review a week before each exam. There's reading quizzes and group work so you kinda need to go to class. My main issue was she didn't use much visual aid; you really need to be a good auditory learner to succeed in class. I liked the movie-viewing hw! She seems pretty passionate about IR.

Law & Politics class is a great option for anyone considering law school. There's lots of reading and exams (take home) take a few days to complete. is passionate in the subject matter and inspirational as a professor. Easy classes, study hard for exams and read the materials.

Professor Steve was a great professor! His lectures are long but most certainly entertaining to watch. Hes a great guy with a good personality. Prof  is so sweet, obviously cares about her students and always responds quickly to emails. You have about 5 assignments per week but they aren't hard and you can get them done in about 1-2 hours. is a very good lecturer that really tried to make sure you understand the world of international relations and american foreign policy. Very engaging and can be surprisingly funny. She was amazing!There were a lot of notes, but her lectures were fun. Also, make sure you pay attention to grammar in your papers. Loved her and her class.

She is just wonderful. So engaged in class with interesting material to lecture on. She doesn't lecture on what is on the textbook so that part is up to you, but the textbook is an easy read.

Extremely helpful and kept the class entertaining.
Wonderful professor. Very informative. His multiple choice tests are extremely hard, but you learn so much.

is an AMAZING professor. Criminal Investigation is the most interesting class I had this semester, and he did a great job of making it easy to understand. She's super great, end of story. Friendly, funny and makes the class interesting. Keeps class engaged and laughing. Lovely lady.

This was probably the best college course I've ever taken; very interesting, lots of new ideas, great teacher. The reading is tough, but he's forgiving on grading IMO. If you do the reading and make an honest effort on the essays you will get a good grade.
I really enjoyed this class and learned some really cool stuff! he is a kind and helpful professor so definitely reach out to him if you need any help or questions.

Nice guy. I took H321 and H508 with him, and both classes were pretty easy. Tests were mostly subjective, and the averages were really high. He wants everyone to do well, and it's not hard to get an A in his classes.

Avoid.
one o my favorite professors eve!

This is my second class was Dr. . Not only are her classes typically pretty easy for upper-division courses, but she is also an amazing person. She will put in extra work to make sure you understand the material.

He is a very good professor. He knows what he is teaching and enjoys it.

Dr.  is extremely nice but I had a really difficult time in this class with exams. There are a lot of easy assignment points and online quizzes but the tests were so hard. The averages of the first 2 tests wer 71% and 63%. I'm hoping for a B- in the class. :-(

is my favorite professor I have had at the college level. I've taken him for Crime Control & Prevention as well as Intro to Law. He is a cool, smooth guy that makes lectures enjoyable. One of the best professors I have had the pleasure of being in class with.

This is my favorite professor so far. She is so wonderful and has an amazing personality. She is always willing to help us. I lov going to each of her classes. She always makes everything so engaging.

a HUGE amount of work for zero payoff. If you miss a class for any reason you can "make up" a missed in-class assignment by writing a 3-5 page paper. is the best. I really loved this course. She is a great teacher and I really learned a lot.

Put it this way: the class ran from 8:30-9:48, and everyone was there pretty much every day. Dr.  was incredibly interesting and really helped me retain information about the subject...I was just taking it as a GEC, but now I'm considering a Psych major. Highly recommended!

I really enjoyed Dr. Ks class. Its a tough class in general but I really liked her approach. Shes a heavy lecturer because theres a lot of material but shes always happy to take small detours to discuss our thoughts on the subjects were going over. Shes very cheerful and tries to make it clear what will be on exams. Be prepared to take notes

Informative lectures that help clarify material from the textbook. Cares about students a lot and is helpful in office hours. I disliked the class itself but the professor was so good that he made it bearable.

Dr.  definitely knows what shes doing; shes clearly knowledgeable on analyzing political arguments. 3440 was extremely reading intensive, but the readings were all valuable and had a clear purpose in the course. Shes super approachable; 10/10 would recommend.

Her lecture isn't the most exciting hour ever but the information she presents is clear. She is extremely understanding and helpful if you need extra help or considerations....just ask in office hours.
I really enjoyed taking this class with professor . The workload was manageable and the course was super interesting.

Dr.  is inexperienced as a political science teacher, but I'm confident she will continue improving. The class was structured in a way that makes getting an A easy, Dr.  is funny and willing to take feedback.. She gives opportunities for extra credit and she works hard to make sure the class discusses many points that may not be popular
Dr.  made an extremely uninteresting class exciting and engaging. She is very knowledgable and always willing to help students out. HIGHLY recommend her!
Great professor! He makes history of psychology so interesting with his sense of humor and his text full of stories. Tests are easy. Beautiful British Accent.

Dr.  sincerely cares about her students a lot and is very accessible outside of class. If you took AP Statistics in high school you'll do great. Attendance is required on chapter practice days. She offers a TON of extra credit opportunities- and no calculation problems on exams. Take this class with her!

is an absolutely wonderful professor! She is very kind and understanding, giving amazing lectures. The simulation was very fun and was one of my favorite parts of the class. Highly suggest taking any class with Professor !

This class includes participation, 45 discussion posts, 3 exams, and an 18-20 page APA style paper. Don't procrastinate on discussion posts, exams almost exclusively cover bolded definitions from the book and class PPTs, and the paper is over a topic of your choice (easy grader). Professor  is a very nice, caring, and knowledgeable teacher.

Prof  is a really great teacher. Helpful with anything you could ever need help with. Instant responses to emails, go out of his way for office hours etc. Lecture can be boring at times, but a lot of political anecdotes. Paper is fairly easy and exams are straight forward. Gives you essays ahead of time to study.

Honestly love  and want to take her again. You do a cool research project all semester and they walk you through it step by step by writing a series of papers. You have to show up to lecture to do well, but her exams were easy and she drops the lowest one. She makes the topic a lot more interesting!
Dr.  is a model Professor.

Professor  is awesome! I learned so much from this class and would definitely take her again. Assignments and tests are straightforward, and there are extra credit opportunities. If you just pay attention during lecture and have a rough understanding of the weekly articles, you'll be fine. Overall this was a very easy class.

Professor  is a really good professor! He always emails back fast, and is very kind when emailing back. His exams are based on in depth responses which the readings are critical to getting a good grade! The quizzes are fair.

Dr.  has a very dry humor and tends to go on tangents, so his lectures are very interesting and funny. You have to complete a few papers and his exams are short answer responses. Overall, you probably don't have to attend class to do well but the lectures can be helpful for specific exam questions. Absolutely would recommend him.
He is a very good teacher and I liked him a lot. Yo will learn and he will reward you with a decent grade if you show up... Good teacher!!!

Professor  is a good teacher. He is very clear when presenting the material and is funny at times. He was also very helpful to those who were having a hard time with the material. There are two papers, which were pretty easy, and three exams which were very difficult. 50% of the exam is from the book while 50% is from the lectures. His exams
Great professor. Really loves to teach. Loved the class. Grades the papers harshly and you definitely have to study for exams because there's a lot of content. Overall though, enjoyed the class.

No book for the class, he posts the necessary readings on Carmen. However, it is possible to go the whole course without reading and still get an A. Focus on his lectures and you'll be fine. Take notes, it makes the midterm and final way easier. Overall, good prof, not too hard, just pay attention and you'll be fine!

This is a fantastic class. If you put in the time to do the readings, and pay attention in class, you'll succeed. 1 Quiz, Midterm, Final, 2 papers, and few other assignments. Attendance is mandatory, but it really isn't that bad because you'll learn about interesting material and are really forced to think critically. One of my favorite classes.
Great professor, easy, willing to help with anything, gives extensions if you contact him

had great online lectures, which led to great notes, which then led to easy assignments. Only had to study twice for this class. Enjoyed her in class lectures too, even if they weren't necessary besides the attendance.

Dr.  is a gentleman. I almost couldn't make it to a midterm because I was stuck in another state, but he let me know we could work things out. I also didn't go to class that often but still got a good grade. As long as you put in the effort, you'll get an easy A for sure.

Great professor.  is highly respected in his field, and his intelligence shines through in class. Classes were split between reading discussions and war games. Papers and projects arent an easy A, but  is always willing to give feedback and offer help before due dates.

I really enjoyed s lectures, they were always very engaging and she explained the concepts very well. She was also very flexible and understanding with students situations and had very sensible late work policy. In my class we were allowed to drop 3 assignments (except really big ones) no questions asked. Any class with her is one worth taking

You don't really have to go to class, attendance isn't mandatory but it will help on tests. I show up to classes, took very little notes and got 100% or above on every tests. All tests are formatted the same and he essentially gives you the test questions beforehand.

Dr.  is a great professor who really knows what he is talking about, and he is really passionate. I just found the class to be really hard for an 'entry level' class. I am not wanting to go into research in psychology, but those who are would really benefit from this class. The quizzes are easy, but the projects are a lot.

Before I took this class I looked in the syllabus and saw that there were various extra credit opportunities. I emailed her various times throughout the semester about extra credit and there was only one assignment. Overall I took this class for the extra credit and ended up with one point off the grade I wanted because there was only one asignm..

I really liked him and this class! Content was interesting and relevant. A decent amount of test prep is required due to the number of studies presented, but go through those and youre golden. Lots of grades with exams, online quizzes, top hat, paper, and extra credit. He listens to student feedback and tries to make lecture interesting.

You get as much out of this class as you get in. Most of the in-class lectures are discussions, and  loves letting the students share their opinions on the topics being discussed in class. He's always available for his office hours, and will talk to you even if you don't have any specific questions.
I think he is a good instructor and very energetic. Besides, I think relating to the current events is useful. Going to the lecture is necessary.

I really enjoyed this course. Lectures did get a little boring at times (not the professors fault, just the information itself.) He incorporates stories and examples that help you understand the material better. The quizzes and discussions are pretty easy as long as you listen to lectures. A very easy but beneficial introduction course!

I took this class to add an extra credit hour to my week. It ended up being very enjoyable, classes weren't every single week, assignments were doable, and the professor cares and is super friendly. Opened my eyes to different kinds of research& you can get to watch Mythbusters! 10/10 would recommend!

I am not a Human Resources major, but I found this class to be very interesting. Lecture isn't "mandatory" but he will give you information for the test that you can't find elsewhere. He makes it very clear what is expected of you. Read the book (very easy to read), go to class, study the slides and you will get an A.

I find  to be an incredible teacher with a thorough understanding of the world around her. She acts 'human' which goes a long way when it comes to learning the material in class. A little disorganized sometimes, but she makes up for it with stimulating lectures and the promotion of open discussions between classmates.

Dr.  is really funny, super smart, and explains hard concepts really clearly. I really loved her class! if you put the work in, you'll get an A, and it's not a ton of work. Readings are all pretty easy, and she goes over them in class, so even if you have trouble, you'll come out understanding it. Tests and quizzes are really fair.

Class dragged on a little but  made it fun. Grade is determined from 3 hw short hw assignments, a survey, 2 midterms, and a comprehensive final. I didn't look at the book once and I got a B+ in the class. Print out the notes, go to lecture, and you will have no problem. Also, her TA is a very sweet girl who is very helpful.

Prof  is very knowledge of welfare state politics and you would learn a lot about different welfare systems from this class. Lots of readings but manageable and she's really caring and flexible with extensions on assignments. 3 exams each worth 25% and ~15 carmen quizzes make up the rest 25%. Not a hard course but you need to put in the work.

I was blown away by how compassionate Dr.  was, and by how open he was to questions. You can tell that he legitimately cares about his students and making sure that you understand the material. The class can be tricky but Dr.  structures lectures so that everyone has a chance to ask any questions, and he works hard to answer them.

Very dedicated to his subject matter. You can tell that Dr.  lives, breathes and eats social psychology. The class is by no means a walk in the park, but if you read the book in tandem with lectures, you'll do fine. On a side note, he indirectly inspired me to pursue a career in education and research.

I started with over a 100% after the first exam, and ended with an A- because its only out of 100 points so every single question on the three tests matters heavily. You don't need to go to lecture because the powerpoints are online. There are a few online quizzes that should be automatic 100s.

I loved this class! He is that rare type of professor that gets you excited about the material. It's clear he loves his subject and he's awesome about answering questions and interacting with the students. Take good notes and you'll do fine.
Great sense of humor.

Weekly assignments due, and he teaches you how to complete them on his lectures that are available on iTunes. You don't have to go to class unless you're struggling and need help. I managed to figure out how to do all of the assignments without showing up to class or asking for help and get an A. Very nice guy, very understanding as well.

Essential if you are considering on becoming a Clinical Psychologist, he teaches you how to critically evaluate research, most of the material is about logic. Rarely used the textbook (just rent it from the library for the assigned readings). Had 5 quizzes at the end of the semester from assigned papers (not textbook). Exams have like 6 essay :(

is THE MAN. One of my favorite professors here at Ohio State. Truly cares about his students and made the subject super interesting. Tests are challenging but he gives you the essay prompts before the exam.
Great lectures, you will learn a good deal about Ohio Politics.

A quiz per week on a video lecture online, then an activity and lab per week. Super organized. Doesn't really teach in person but somehow I learned a lot. Group project and individual paper are big parts of grade. Exams are not bad if you look at the study guides. I had 0 experience coding before this class and now I feel like I have a strong base

I loved attending this class. He made the material really interesting, and easy to understand. He's probably one of the best professors i've ever had. There's no point in buying the book, everything is in the slides. I would definitely recommend him!

First thing to note: this class has a different grading scale: A 88%, A- 85%, and so on. Second thing: he doesn't go off any textbook, instead using his own PowerPoint slides. My advice: either print off the slides and take notes on them during lecture or take notes on your laptop and transfer them to printed slides to study. Helped a lot.
One of the best professors at OSU

Dr.  is extremely considerate and thorough. You know exactly what is going to happen and when it will happen. I knew when I signed up for his class that I would need to miss some days of class and he was very helpful in allowing me to make up missed work and assignments prior to leaving. Anything on tests/quizzes are discussed in class.

Dr.  is a straight-up professor. She doesn't cut any slack and she demands hard work. She expects class participation and grades each student on his or her involvement with the subjects being discussed. If you read the assigned coursework (not really optional), do your homework, and participate in class discussions, then you should do well.

If you are wanting to pursue graduate school/ phD / PsyD in clinical psych, take this course! I found the material to be absolutely fascinating. Looks at a lot of research, identifies key problems in the growing field of clin psych, prepares you for furthering your education. A good amount of reading, but never just "busy work". Smart and nice prof

love love love this prof. her lectures are interesting and she knows with extreme detail what she is talking about. she makes classes interesting by addressing relevant issues. always willing to go out of her way to help students if they need it. take her! friends had her for h101 and they liked her too!
Best prof I have every had in college. Cares about students. Difficult tests, but relevant, and if you do the work, you will do fine in his classes. Great sense of humor. Makes learning fun.

Dr. Sullivan is a gem. She clearly is passionate about the subject matter, and her heart for the students and content is evident. She is passionate and intelligent, and I learned so much without really trying.
Goes very quickly but explains things well and gives partial credit on tests.

He will do whatever he can to help you get an A. You can redo all quizzes and assignments (which are all open note anyways) and he even does quizzes with the entire class together and gives everyone full credit. All lectures are available on zoom and as long as you pay attention you should get an A.

Midterm (35%), final (35%) (noncumulative) and paper (30%). Gives out very detailed study guides for the exams which have around 40 MC questions and 10-15 short answer. Paper is over a famous court trial in the 20th century. Material covered in class is very interesting. Focused on the criminal justice system. Put in the time in and get the grade.

Wasnt my favorite class but dr.  was very kind and helpful. I took this class online and there were weekly readings, lecture notes and quizzes. Then there are 2 essays and a final project. Everything was fairly easy and theres a lot of extra credit. If you think you deserved a higher grade on the essay, just ask him to look it over again

Dr.  is super funny and very nice. He cares for his students! Quizzes each week (not many questions so don't feel nervous) and it's based on his lectures mainly so really focus on that! Easy class fr and interesting, I def recommend it!!
Lectures were very long and did not always stay on point.It helps to have a good TA because I found that my notes from lecture weren't all that helpful on the midterm.

The class have a lot of memorization. However, the exams are straightforward and have extra credit. Print slides before class and/or add notes from his lecture to the slides. He only focuses on important points and some exam questions are from his lecture (not on slides). He didn't really agree with textbook sometimes. One presentation assignment.
Though it's been nearly 5 years, I often refer to what I learned in this class in discussions with colleagues.

Class consisted of asynchronously watching a lecture and videos each week and then 1 page reflections about what you watch. In person meetings were a lot of cool guest lecturers and discussions about topics. Not very much work, no tests. 1 group research paper and 1 "final" project that is really easy
She is an alright professor. Studying is an absolute in her class. Material is easy. Most tests are all multiple choice.
I loved this class. I looked forward to it everyday I had it. Although you don't get lots of one on one time with Dr.  she has such a passion that it is very enjoyable.

1 Paper, 2 Exams. Each exam had so much content. The exams overall are easy if you can remember 8-9 weeks of content. The lectures are around 50 slides each so each exams has an enormous amount of slides. The class is quite repetitive and you can get lost in the amount of information. Lectures are dry. Paper exams. Only around 2 questions of EC.
Dr.  is an amazing professor. She definitely cares about your performance in class and will do almost anything to help you be better and understand more. I would 100% take her class again!

I really can't say enough about this professor. I found her to be very intelligent and engaging, and I found the course material to be relevant and applicable as a great intro to law. The reading is the lecture, and the lecture is very well structured. Attend the class. If you do the work in this class, you get the grade.

No surprises on the midterms. The final was not cumulative. Had to write one research paper- START AS EARLY AS POSSIBLE. Got really good feedback on the paper from Dr.  before turning it in which was very helpful. Show up to class and study the notes given in class. Reading the textbook helped me but I could still have done as will without it

is a wonderful professor. You can count on her to follow through on everything that she says. She is honest and hard working, and expects the same from you. I learned so much from her, and hope to have her again!

Dr.  is an incredibly sweet professor who truly cares about his students success, and is clearly loved by a lot of students. Unfortunately, I found his lecture slides to be dry and confusing to follow, which made studying for exams a bit difficult for me. Aside from the exams, he's a pretty easy grader on papers and discussion boards.
Fantastic!!!!

Wonderful Professor.Very smart,very friendly and helpful.Will bend over backwards to help students and while his class is not easy,you'll learn a lot about foreign policy decision making. Great class.
Great class. I learned a lot about myself and useful things that I will use in my relationships. Tests were challenging but the assignments and project were fun to do.

Makes class fun by mixing lectures with powerpoints, discussions, and debates. Other than the readings, the only assignments all quarter are participating in one debate, 2 3-5 page papers, and the final which she is considering making take home. She likes to keep things interesting and wants you to have a good time. Definitely worth your time!
Take advantage of all extra credit opportunities and study for the exams. He gives you the power point slides, but be sure to take extra notes on them.

Really clear lectures with outlines available online. Super important to show up to class and at the very least skim the book. Prepare for the tests using the study guide she gives a week in advance and its pretty hard not to do well.

This class is NOT hard. One midterm, three one page assignments, 40% final. Go to class, skim the book, notes online. She is easy to listen to and presents the material in an interesting way. Easier than some of my GECs. Would highly recommend.

This class is NOT hard. One midterm, three one page assignments, 40% final. Go to class, skim the book, notes online. She is easy to listen to and presents the material in an interesting way. Easier than some of my GECs. Would highly recommend.

Professor  is a very approachable professor and will take whatever time out of his day that he has to help you understand the material. His exams are hard, but he will offer regrades if you defend your answers. He genuinely loves to teach and explains the material in depth

For such an early class, it was the one I never wanted to skip. His lectures were always equally as entertaining as they were informational. His experience in the field and his advice were helpful to anyone considering becoming a psychologist. However, his quizzes are a little difficult so make sure you study! Attendance is also SUPER important!!

Professor  was a pretty good instructor and she kept class fun. The only complaint I have is I don't feel like she did a very good job preparing us for the final. Since there were no exams during the quarter, I didn't really know what to expect of the final. Other than that she was great!

DeKay is a nice guy and can be helpful. Spends all of his class time lecturing and can go on and on about one topic for a really long time. Out of touch with technology for someone teaching a stats class that uses programming. Assumes that you know all of the basics already even though it's a foundational stats class.

4 exams. She allows an 8.5x11 page of notes for exams which is quite helpful. Posts notes online, but you need to go to lecture to understand them. She gives you review questions for exams which help alot. She also curves exams. One hw assignment every week dropped the lowest 4. ALEKS hw wasnt bad. Gives out extra credit for going to class.

Truly an amazing person. Overall, the class content is very easy to understand, and watching her lecture slides prior to the lecture was plenty for the quizzes. Everything was open-note and pretty simple. Just do the assignments and you will be very successful!

Very very sweet woman! Posts the cutest weekly update videos for the class. Lots of the grading/lecturing is done by the TAs, but Prof  was very quick to answer any emails/questions I had. Not a very difficult class, the weekly assignments definitely forced me to learn the material and were sometimes long but never really hard!
Dr.  is one of the best profs I've ever had! I'm in my senior year and her classes are great.

The greatest prof. I have ever had. It is clear what she expects from you so if you do what she says, the classes are pretty easy. If you take notes from her power points, there is no reason you shouldn't do well on the exams. She is younger, so I think that she understands the students more. Always willing to help, or just talk if you want.
She is the reason I want to study Psychology!.....A wonderful & very talented prof. Her test are not easy ....but you will learn a lot. I enjoy all her classes!.......
Interesting and easy class. Professor is a great guy!

This class is really manageable and interesting! Dr.  is very approachable and kind. Make sure to go to lecture, as TH is important for your grade and there are in-person activities that will tank your grade if you miss them. Just go to class, do your assignments - and you'll get an A.

Dr.  is by far one of the most amazing professors i've had. He understands and as a Psych major he makes the material interesting and is consistently making students get up and get involved in class to keep us awake. I'd totally take his class again. It's amazing.

Prof.  is the most grounded and personable professor I've ever had. I have ADHD and I can confidently say that his lectures are amazingly engaging, I've never been bored in his class. He exudes so much passion through his lectures that it's frankly hard to not do well in his class. Overall, one of the best learning experiences in my life.

Professor  is a thoroughly outstanding instructor who took a real interest in my success. She strikes a careful balance between imparting information and allowing free discussion. If I could repeat this class every quarter, I would (and I'd bet I'd learn something new every time!) I cannot speak highly enough of the overall experience.

I thought this class was really interesting, and Deb did a great job making it fun and engaging. I won't lie, this is one of the hardest classes I've taken at OSU, and Deb is a really strict grader. You have three assignments, quizzes, and tests for the entire semester so you basically have to do well on all of them if you want a good grade.
Charles is such a good professor, who is understanding and kind. He goes out of his way to make sure us students are successful in his class! I recommend taking him!!

Dr.  was very kind in her feedback, though I never interacted with her in person. Her class was easy and the criteria was clear while learning a lot. It was a great intro class, not too intense but I learned enough.

For Cognitive Neuroscience, lectures are very dry and basically consist of her reading off lecture slides (which you can study online) and throwing in barely class-related comics or videos. Took me about 5 lectures to realize that you're much better off reading lecture slides on your own time. I got an A by just studying 3 hours total per exam.

He is clear in telling students what he expects from them. His exams can be moderately hard if you expect that memorizing things will get you off with a good grade (don?t write note cards prior to exams). Study the concepts from the book and make sure that you revise his lecture notes.

Dr  is a nice professor. His teaching is clear and notes are organized. He is open to his class and open to many questions. Even if you haven't registered the class for some reason but still want to go to the class for some topics, he is still OK with that. A really responsible instructor.

is an amazing professor and you should definitely take his classes. He is extremely clear and really wants his students to succeed. Asking questions after class and taking advantage of office hours is a good resource for his classes because he is super helpful one on one. Test questions are clearly worded and he gives tons of resources.

Kind of a hard class. The second midterm was really hard for most students, but he ended up curving the class in the end. He didn't do a great job of teaching the material for the second midterm, and the TA's weren't very helpful when we asked questions about the material either. In the end it worked out, but still a tough class to get through.

Must read book and attend class to understand and to be able to get lecture notes, which is where the midterm questions come from. Okay class, worth 2 days a week for GEC credits if you can pay attention to lecture in class

The class was a positive experience, but could get dry sometimes. She read pretty much directly off the slides, but attendance was a must because we would have surprise in-class assignments which counted as an attendance grade. Grading criteria for her assignments could have been a bit clearer, but she was friendly and responsive to emails.

Hands down the best professor I've ever had. She teaches you so much and in such an original way with the simulations, and though her midterms can be a bit difficult, she goes out of her way to make sure everyone that works hard ultimately succeeds. I wish I could take all of my classes with her, honestly.

Chip is a really nice guy and knows how to explain the material and give good examples. He doesn't give out extra credit and there are only 3 exams, 10 quizzes and 5 CREP experiment points but the material is common sense and easy to grasp. He also gives you a chance to take everything a second time and get the average of your scores.

Dr.  is one of the best professors at OSU. Truly one of the nicest, most knowledgeable, and helpful professors I've had. Not an easy A but wont make you cry yourself to sleep. Not an overwhelming amount of work but covers a lot of material. He does not use any notes and lecture is completely oral, which is an adjustment but helped me focus.

Professor  is knowledgeable on what she is teaching. The lectures will keep you interested and you will be able to tell that she knows what she is talking about. The issue that many people did have is that the course was too difficult for a 2000 level course. There was just a few assignments to be graded on and expected to know so much.

Three quizzes, three exams. Final exam is noncumulative. Very direct and to the point. Randomly passes around a sign-in sheet to gauge attendance. NOTE: If you're under 18, you have to write EIGHT summaries of research papers to get research credit (10% of grade). If you're over 18, you get to participate in experiments for that credit instead.

Lectures were very long, often 40 mins to an hour (which was hard to sit through considering it was an online class and there were no closed caption available). His homework assignments were weighed a lot so if you missed one your grade would tank. However exams weren't too difficult, a lot of memorization but that was it.

is a really great instructor. He really cares about his students and hes really accessible. The content is awesome if youre into developmental psych and its a really laid back upper level psych course since exams are straightforward, easy, and dont count for much of the grade. Highly recommend him if youre looking for an easy A.

Dr.  was awesome. Genuinely enjoyed his class. He's so funny and his sense of humor is perfect for engaging college kids. Attendance isn't mandatory and lectures are recorded which is great. Exams are all multiple choice and totally fair. Easy class for Neuro majors.

cares very much for her students and is passionate about the material she teaches. She is on top of emails and willing to meet with students however she can. Three exams and a research project are the major grades. The project isn't bad, but the exams can be difficult if you don't study. Attendance is not mandatory, but I would recommend it.

The class was fairly easy, though I already had some background knowledge. He posts his lectures from the previous year online so you can skip class and not miss much. Only worth going to class for current events, which do show up on exams. 3 exams and a paper, but no study guides for the exams. Questions can be kind of specific.

Like the comments below,  is an incredible professor with as much experience and knowledge as you'd ever expect to find at OSU. His class is very professional and he treats the students like adults. That means he expects a lot from you. It's a great class, just make sure you leave plenty of time to do the work, cause there's a lot of it.

Great class! A lot of reading, but it's worth it if you are interested in political theory. Assignment feedback was very helpful, especially on papers. He made a graduate level class accessible to all of the students who took it (including undergrads and Program 60 students). Very understanding about his students' pandemic-related struggles, too.

Best professor I've had at OSU, very helpful and approachable and great sense of humor. Tests are near impossible, he expects you to think on the level of grad students, which is not unreasonable for a high level course, but still takes you off guard.
Good professor. Made the lectures exciting and worth going to. A lot of textbook/book reading for a gen ed, but otherwise very interesting.

Very enthusiastic about psychology and really engages the audience. I took his online class and he posted videos of all his lectures and the powerpoints he used. He could not have been more clear of what was expected from the students.

I thought this class was fantastic. Dr. Monetmayor is very interesting and presents the information very clearly. Reading the book is a must and the tests are challenging but I would definitely recommend this class.

Dr.  is such a genuine human and professor! Her class is easy and straightforward, consisting of discussion boards and article summaries. I had an issue with COAM for another class as she and my other class had the same prompt of writing my personal immigration history. She was so understanding and even wrote a letter advocating for me.

This was my first class as a non-trad student after being out of school for 8 years. I found Dr. 's lectures interesting and relevant to the real world. He uses a lot of stories which were interesting to me. Half of the tests are from the text, so there is a lot of reading involved. If you go to class and read the text, you can get an A.
Was the sweetest man I have ever had as a teacher. Very understanding and class was great and easy.

's class was super easy, 4 quizzes and 2 papers. I enjoyed the material we went over and  clearly really cares about his students. Lectures and grading were super laid back and it was a very easy A. Occasionally had in class assignments but I still did fine missing a few days. Would highly recommend taking any of 's classes!

Lectures are difficult to follow since they randomly just jump around subjects. He posts his slides online so I just printed them and took notes on the print outs. For the final I read all the readings he assigned in about two days and got a A on it since most of the essay questions were from the readings.

Pretty easy class while still learning a lot.  is a really good story teller so his lectures are pretty interesting. The review sessions before the midterm and final covered everything and the paper is broken down so its not very hard.

Dr.  was the best professor I have had yet at OSU. Dr.  does a phenomenal job bridging the basics to detailed aspects of the complex topics
 discussed. He really emphasizes learning and understanding the concepts by allowing TWO makeups per assessment/reflection/quiz. Everything in this class is open book/notes. Take with a grain of salt

This is actually the most interesting class I have taken in OSU. If you are really into social psych, you would like this class. There's no assignments, so final grade is only dependent on exams, which are hard but the grade is curved according to the ranking. Attendance is not mandatory but super helpful if you want to get a good grade.

The nicest guy I've ever met and my favorite professor at OSU--favorite teacher I've ever had. You won't find anyone who cares more about their subject and it shows. Always takes time to answer questions and entertain the ideas of every student. Couldn't recommend him highly enough.

is a very nice professor. He will answer any and every question you have and is overall very helpful. He seems to be an easy grader. I highly recommend him.

He is so understanding and flexible! This course is particularly stressful for many people because of the content, but he makes every effort to keep everyone safe.

I really enjoyed 's class. His lectures are very straightforward and the exam questions are taken straight from his powerpoints/lectures. I felt like his explanations during class were very helpful so I recommend going to class. Not too work outside of class either. I recommend !

Great Professor. Made lectures very interesting, and always was willing to answer questions. He really cares about his students and what he is teaching. Exams were fairly tough and detailed, but everything was from the slides.
A lot of notes.....Study Guide on Carmen really helps for exams.... really hard grader....she does really try to help her students

Prof.  is the best professor Ive ever had at OSU as far as what I learned in the class but the class was not easy! I loved the content, but there were only 3 exams, completely essay-based and timed. Dr.  taught such an amazing class. I learned so much and the assignments were sort of fun. We had a presentation and paper and I actually sort of enjoyed those. I highly recommend her! I took three classes (Sociology 2330, 4508, and 4610) with her and she is an amazing professor. She cares about her students and her classes are very interesting.

Class was informative but super easy. You get out what you put into it - the lectures and readings are long and interesting, but you really don't need them to do fine with the weekly work. I probably spent like an hour on class each week, plus a couple hours for the final paper. Would recommend.

Dr.  was great. Unfortunately with 2020 he had some family complications come up and had to go off schedule but he was always great at communicating that and was very lenient with grading. Class is very lecture heavy and youre graded by a few things. Overall it was a great class and Id be happy to take a course with him again.

He is very caring of his students and wants his students to learn. This is a project class and graded by few things. Little to do outside of class, and class is mandatory unless you don't mind making up in class labs and activities. Good Professor
Really enjoyed the subject matter and made his students want to learn and enjoy it as well. More conceptual than memorization. Takes random participation points.

Lectures are really interesting and usually funny/entertaining. He gives out a paper at the beginning of every unit with exact specifics of what you'll be tested on. Attendance is barely a requirement as he posts all his lectures online at the beginning of the semester.
One of the best professors I had at CSCC. Dr.  is caring, understanding and most importantly I like the way she teaches. If you do your work you will get an easy A class.

Dr.  is a great professor, his lectures are always amazing and very interesting. You only have three tests and a final exam and then assignments in class. He will ask questions on the tests that you did't cover in class sometimes so read your book, but it is a good class!
Dr.  is an amazing professor. He uses personal examples to make us understand. I would recommend him to everyone. Best professor I have ever had!

This is a great class and if you put in effort you can do well.

Dr.  was an amazing lecturer! A really awesome instructor!!! I am a junior majoring in Psych and will take every class I can with . She makes class fun and genuinely cares about her students.She adds a little personality to her lectures with excerpts from her life. I LOVE her dearly! A+++++ professor!

Professor  was great for POLISCI 3910. She utilized both lectures and discussions to keep students engaged. She's also extremely caring and wants students to do well. She's friendly and approachable, and I enjoyed taking her class. No textbook, but a lot of reading in her class, mainly research articles for group projects. Professor  was amazing!! A lot of particpation so attendance is a must!! But you'll find yourself wanting to go to learn about the day's discussion and subject! She was always bright and cheery and really made the class quite delightful!

Professor MacGilvray is not only an amazing professor but also a great human being. His class is very inspiring and very heavily test-based but he does curve the score to your advantage every time. I loved Deb so much. This class was not easy, but it was so interesting. You will have to put in a lot of work, but because of Deb I fell in love with the content and wanted to do the work. Class wasn't too hard and she puts lectures online so you can print them out. There are quite a few homeworks but they are mostly easy and you get 2 tries on them, so they just boost your grade since the only others are the 2 midterms and a final.

Despite the ratings here, I think Professor  is one of the best psych professors in OSU. He ensures that you truly understand the material, and spares no effort in teaching you. theres a quiz, discussion and lecture assignment due every week, must submit discussion by saturday or 2 points are taken for "late" work even though the due date is sunday. make sure to watch lectures for midterms/finals because he often had questions pertaining to what he says in lecture.

Awesome teacher. The homework takes time and you have to learn how to edit the codes he gives you if you don't want to spend 8+ hours on each assignment. Dr.  is extremely caring and understands that we are humans, not everything goes our way. At the end of the semester, he gave everyone two weeks to turn in anything they may have missed. I took this class as an online Diversity GE, and it was very interesting! workload is quite manageable each week as well. Amazing teacher! Keeps lectures interesting and is so extremely helpful in making sure you understand everything!!!

Dr.  is awesome. He is passionate about the material and his student's success. He makes a real effort to get to know everyone in the class and to offer constructive feedback. was an excellent lecturer. Insightful, even handed, and willing to answer questions and have a discussion. The class was based mostly on the midterms, final and paper, but he gave a generous curve and graded fairly. I really enjoyed this class.

Dr.  has a ton of cool experience he brings to the course. I think for some the material could be dry, but he made it so interesting. Take this class, it is challenging enough but interesting as well.  is a wonderful prof and super helpful if you go to office hours. If you are a poli sci major at OSU, do no miss out!

One of the best teachers I've taken! Great lectures and super easy exams. Noncumalative final, attendance points, and discussion posts are the only grades so not much work. Great teacher and interesting material
Dr.  is one of my favorite professors at OSU! Definitely take a class with her if you get the chance.
Absolutely awesome professor- would take him again, for sure! made class interesting every day...i learned SO much in this class...he is the best professor i have ever had!

Dr. DEFINITELY knows her stuff! Have taken more than one class with her and she is just totally awesome! She repeats herself 3 times during note taking so there is no way you can't keep up. EASY notes and interesting, fun lectures. She is EXTREMELY willing to help you succeed in her classes!

Prof.  is probably one of the best, if not the best, instructor I've ever had. He's very informed and the love for his subject really comes out. She takes random attendance - so go to every class. She talks really fast & studdars so I recommend you record her lectures. Her lectures are 90% graphs that will be translated to 50 or 100 question multiple choice. No curve and only 4 assignments (2 exams & 2 papers) for the whole semester.

I loved Dr. ! She removed a lot of material that gave students trouble in the past and constantly went at a pace she felt the class was understanding. Very straightforward of what is required and a fairly easy class if you just show up and pay attention.
is great! This was one of my favorite classes, 2 tests worth 10 and 15% of your grades. Weekly assignments with really clear directions, no class on Fridays. Would really recommend this class.

Professor  was an awesome professor. I had her in Summer 2020, so things were a bit odd with the new online schooling but she made everything you need easily accessible. By far my favorite professor! She is so easy going and understanding. You can easily get over 100% in the class. I will be taking 3 other classes with her next semester based off of the great experience that I had! I recommend!

Dr.  is my favorite professor at OSU. Her lectures are much more discussion based, which some people may not like, but I really enjoyed it. Vlad is a great professor. His course requires a decent amount of work, but it's very interesting. Some units were more stimulating than others , though. It's also worth noting that a lot of extra credit is given out. Overall, I would highly recommend this course.

Professor  has been one of my favorite professors at Ohio State so far. He makes the class really enjoyable and he is funny. The greatest Math professors in Math department. He explains math concepts clearly and did many examples in class which helps a lot. Exams are fair and he graded it fairly. Just do the homework you will do well in this class.

good teacher. has lots of notes. but covers everything needed in class.very nice and funny professor. very open to going off on tangents and class discussions. not an easy class but an enjoyable one. highly recommend.

This class was very enjoying and I learned a lot from it. We rarely had homework and honestly, I finished most of the week's work in an hour. Definitely recommend taking ay class you can with this professor.

Awesome professor! Interesting class, AND a very easy A!Despite the easy tests, you learned a lot in this class. Study the study guide and you'll enjoy the class without stressing yourself out. The class was definitely a challenge, but Professor  was kind and always willing to help out students.

He's really funny and makes lectures pretty interesting and fun which made me look forward to going to class. Very interactive with the students during class and clarifies the material better than the textbook does. The book is necessary for both the exams and online quizzes.

Dr.  is extremely caring and exceedingly smart. Her class is engaging and expects engagement from students as well. Grading was fair and extra credit was abundant.

Few homeworks and quizzes, but they're not too hard and there's a lot of help available. The material involves a small amount of statistics, but really not deeper than introductory knowledge. This is my second time having this professor and I really appreciate the format with which she organizes her classes. Lectures are group-oriented and there is a lot of interaction. This professor is a fair grader and is always in a joyful mood.

Great class to take. Very engaging in lectures. Papers are not too difficult as long as you follow his instructions. Tests are very easy if you read the required material and actually engage in lecture.

Absolutely loved Dr. ! She is a fair grader with great feedback. You will need the book (you will use it for online quizzes & HW). I definitely recommend this class!

Dr.  is amazingly accomplished and a great lecturer. She really knows her material; her powerpoints and lectures make the material very clear especially for tests and papers. The class is easy if you go and pay attention.

Great professor. I just loved the way he talked and it was my most favorite class taken so far. Although an easy GE, he actually made me interested in the subject. I looked forward to every class. Also, it wasn't hard with only a few hours of studying before each midterm.

Super nice! easy grader and explains the material well! Review handouts helps alot on the exam. Reading is a must!

Good teacher, great person. Willing to go above and beyond to help students. Left me a note on my homework asking if I wanted any advice on applying to graduate schools, without me asking her beforehand.

Dr.  is a caring and passionate teacher and makes sure his students stay engaged and succeed. Math 3345 content is very proof-based and not always the most interesting for non-math majors, but he does his best. His lectures are very helpful and exams and homework is fair. Class may be difficult if it's your first time doing proofs.

He was super nice and caring, and always accessible outside of class. He often gave us hints for potential exam questions, which was very helpful. 2 midterms and a final, with multiple choice and choice of short answer. I found his lectures to be pretty engaging and he was happy to answer questions as class went along. I would take his class again!

Dr.  has great lectures that include a variety of material like slides, videos, charts, and examples that we look at in class. She allows a front&back page of notes on exams, uses TopHat for reading questions, and had 3 1-page papers throughout the semester. She's available after class for questions and encourages discussion in class.
Extremely bright professor, very knowledgable, and always willing to go above and beyond to help students understand the material. Would take another class with Dr.  in a heartbeat.

One of the most enjoyable classes Ive had at osu. The homework is always easy and interesting. Quizzes were all open note with no time limit and she offers extra credit. Dr  is quick to answer emails and her lectures were always enjoyable to sit through.

I really like Professor Edwards. She was very nice, helpful, and straightforward. There were a couple papers, a midterm, a final, and then a big final project that was a lot of work, but not that hard. The midterm and final were not that easy, but she didn't grade too tough on the project. I recommend this class, even as a GE.

Amazing class and professor who had some great stories from his own experiences. He made the class fun and engaging. Attendance matters as he takes it randomly throughout the semester, but I had a great time so never skipped.

Requires decent effort to do well in the class. Weekly quizzes, 1 midterm, 1 non-cumulative final, 1 term paper, extra credit on research survey & weekly discussion. However, the class is enjoyable, and if you can relate the class materials to what's on the news and media, you will do well. Plus, hompson is caring and helpful at times.

Dr. is a phenomenal instructor and keeps the class engaged. She provides clear instructions and keeps everything organized. She provides excellent feedback on papers and she gives great advice about research.
Exceptional professor and made one of my first classes at OSU enjoyable!
She gives every opportunity to do well in this class and to communicate with her as an instructor. Highly recommend!
Hard class and long homeworks. Need to be willing to put time into studying for midterm and final. Homework usually averaged 8 hours and required SAS code understanding. Office Hours helpful!

By far one of my favorite professors at OSU. His class had challenging material, but none of the assignments or exams are extremely difficult and he is great about implementing feedback. He also gave an easy extra credit assignment. I wish I had taken more classes with him while at OSU.

She is very interested in making sure the students understand the topics and how they react to the studies. She is objective yet structured in her teachings. Class was fun and stimulating. I would recommend this class and teacher to a friend.

Dr.  is one of the best professors I've had at OSU. She was very effective at teaching about the welfare state from a global standpoint and gave me a much deeper understanding of the welfare state here in the US, which is something I believe we all need to understand. This is one of my only classes where I genuinely enjoyed the reading.

Amazing professor! Creates a great balance between professionalism and fun (humor) in the classroom. Material is very relevant to current affairs. He's always very accessible, and is always willing to help. He's a Prof. Emeritus, so take a class with him while he's still at the University!

Dr. T is one of my favorite professors I've ever had. His lectures are super interesting and he constantly tells first hand stories that keep the student super engaged. He is also very caring and will gladly help any student outside of class with career opportunities or class work. He is very passionate, which causes students to be passionate too.

Dr.  is wonderful! Her lectures were exceptionally well-organized with clear information and lots of real-world examples. I appreciated how she worked in relevant cultural topics and integrated science + society together. Outside of class, she prioritizes communication and is accessible to answer questions and provide guidance.

Mary is the best professor I've had. She is incredibly kind and understanding, so it's okay to miss class- but the material is SUPER important to get. Plan on going every lecture. The readings and topics can be difficult, but she is a phenomenal and engaging lecturer. Always well-prepared. Fascinating class! Fair grading.

Dr.  is a great prof! She is very straight forward and provides detailed study guides. Her lectures provide just the right amount of material needed to succeed on tests. Textbook reading is optional. In-class activities once a week for attendance. Very friendly and approachable! Also allows you to drop a test which is very helpful.
Best professor I have had in my 3 years at Ohio State. He's such a caring person who wants his students to succeed and learn the material. Lots of papers for this course but all worth it.

Dr. 's class was pretty interesting. I appreciated the fact that her lecture videos managed to be succinct while covering almost everything we needed to know. There were quizzes every other week, which were usually pretty easy if you watched the lectures and read the textbook, and the HW was generally easy points, too. Definitely recommend!

Dr.  is a great professor and professional. He is very supportive of his students while keeping an engaging course. He continues to support his students even after they have moved on from his course in professional matters.

Best professor. Chapter quizzes through Pearson (I finished all of mine in one day), 3 exams (all easy As), 10 discussion posts (easy), 1 final paper, 1 bonus paper, and bonus points on each exam. Really great class, you can work ahead, and will pass with an A. Genuine feedback and I highly recommend. I took it SU21, asynchronous and online.

Wish more of my online classes were like hers. Simple, straightforward format with lectures that were just the right length, and plenty of opportunities to practice for exams and ask questions. Also loved the fact that she talked about students' research interests during office hours! She' great at communicating and responds to emails quickly, too.

Dr.  has great lectures that included slides, videos, charts, and examples. She allows a front&back page of notes on exams, uses TopHat for feedback & getting-to-know-you questions, gives 3 1-pagers throughout the sem, 3 extra credit assignments, is available after class, will meet to discuss exam grades, & encourages discussion in class.
Excellent teacher. Enjoys and knows his subject matter. Friendly and helpful.

One of the best courses I have had here at OSU! Dr.  is an excellent professor and I would take anything that she taught. The lectures were engaging and fun. Not your average poli sci class, she teaches using a variety of disciplines and challenges you to think for yourself. Very helpful in office hours and gives points back on exams.
Dr. is humble instructor and an approachable instructor. He explains everything clearly and makes class entertaining. He is happy to answer questions and give clear feedback.

The best professor I have had during this pandemic! Lots of little assignments, but the lectures are pre-recorded and she didn't give us a final paper like she had planned to help us out. Really cares about her students and their well being. We need more professors like this at OSU.

Wonderful professor - clear, concise, and really good at conveying the the material and making it relative. She will go out of her way to help any student who is putting forth a legitimate effort. I highly recommend her!
Very nice, clear lectures, extremely helpful and took time to help anyone who needed it. By far one of my best teachers.

Very smart and funny too! I would take another class with her. She is willing to answer questions. She doesn't assign much work but the work she does assign is interesting. She keeps class fun and wants her students to have a good time while learning. A valuable asset to OSU Mansfield!

Dr.  is wonderful! Very helpful with questions and very knowledgeable. Very kind and caring for students. Lectures were interactive and fun. Only 1 chapter and 3 hours of lecture a week. Discussions were very fun. Highly recommend taking Dr. 's class. Quizzes ask stuff from his lectures while Exams focus primarily on book content.

Dr.  is one of the best professors I have had at Ohio State. Her lectures are fun, hilarious, and interactive. Her exams are also relatively easy if you prepare before. I would HIGHLY recommend doing the readings, as the essay questions on her exams almost always pertain to them. I would take another class with her again if I could!

Doug has been my favorite professor at OSU so far. He really cares a lot about his students and makes the effort to engage everyone. He goes through slides very quickly and the tests sometimes have pretty specific questions, but if you go to all the labs/classes, take good notes, study, and ask questions during the tests it's not hard to get an A!

Dr.  is extremely knowledgeable in the topics he teaches and is very generous with extra credit opportunities. The course itself is test heavy (4 exams) but his are not cumulative and they're over less than 5 subjects each.  is very enthusiastic and encourages students to ask questions to make sure they understand the material!

Favorite class taken at OSU. She cared about students ands always available when help was needed. She lets you drop 1 out of 3 tests and the final is very straight forward. The entire class is very strait forward and although there is a lot of info, Dr.  is passionate about it. She is the best professor to take this class with.

Absolutely LOVE this professor. Always available during office hours and if you have a want to get a good grade and are willing to put in the time he will certainly work with you! Had an issue one semester where I missed over a month of class and he was more than willing to work with me to ensure I was able to pass the class. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!

Joe made a relatively difficult subject very easy to understand. This was my first exposure to mathematical proofs and I'm very glad I had Joe as a lecturer. The exams were very fair and he's a caring person in general so I would definitely recommend.

Dr. Mike is such a great and inspirational lecturer to have. Hes super helpful and understanding, and challenges you to think for yourself. The class was heavy in terms of coursework (it was over six weeks) but very manageable. If you do the readings and attend the lectures then youll learn a great deal from this class and earn an easy A.

This professor was absolutely amazing. If you are interested in Public Health, or in taking a class with a respectful, driven, caring, and enthusiastic professor, then take this course. I took this course right before USMLE step 1 as a medical student and it was still worth every second. Amazing course, and really amazing professor.

Loved Dr. 's caring and positive engergy. The professor provided advice for graduate school that helped me in my entrance interviews. Being able to select my own topic and work on my own research led me to discover my desired area of focus in psychology. Highly recommend and would take again if I wasn't graduating.

This is by far the best class I've taken at Ohio State so far. She is extremely helpful and very funny. I recommend office hours simply because her TAs and she give very helpful hints for the exams. I don't really enjoy the subject matter (this is just a required course) but she makes it interesting and fun to learn. Highly recommend.

Dr.  is very kind and makes an effort to get to know all of the students. She's very interested in helping students, and the class is easy enough if you do all the assignments. There are online lectures weekly that are used for the quizzes, and a final poster project that builds throughout the semester. I would recommend taking Dr. .

Dr. T is truly one of the best professors in the sociology department at OSU. He is very knowledgable and genuinely cares for all of his students. He is a fair grader and his course material is very interesting- he knows how to keep a class engaged and his classes have always been my favorite.

I love Professor 's class. He's always ready to help, provides great resources, and his lectures are engaging. The quizzes are frequent and the pre-class readings are many, but they prepare you well for the exams. His passion for the subject and dedication to his students is what makes this course amazing. Overall, he's a great professor.

Dr.  was an amazing instructor! She always teaches the information clearly and makes the topic fun to learn. I learned a lot from this class. Professor  was passionate about both the course material as well as helping her students. I am very happy I took it as I learned a lot.

One of the best classes I've taken at OSU. Participation and attendance matter for your grade. Class is very structured with reading quizzes (which you can do online) and a group project. He uses a lot of videos to aid his lectures, which I found helpful. Overall Vlad  is a very good, straightforward teacher.
Dr.  wants the best for her students. Very helpful and understanding. One of the best Psych Professors at OSU Newark. Must attend class for assignments and possible extra credit opportunities.

Dr.  is a true asset to Ohio State. His lectures are interesting. He has a great sense of humor, enjoys teaching, and his experience outside of the classroom really helps you apply what your learning. Show up for class, make note cards of the lectures, and you'll get an A. He assigned 3 math oriented assignments and 15 half page briefs.

This is my second course with Dr.  and I wish I could take a third! Dr.  is kind and compassionate. She is clear with her assignment requirements and wants her students to succeed. Dr. 's class brightened my day. If you take her course, attend lectures to fully benefit from her teaching!

Such an easy A and she is honestly the best! Her lectures are so interesting and there is an extra credit assignment worth 3%. The 2 papers are relatively easy and she is very willing to help and give feedback if you need it. Definitely recommend!!

Dr.  was pretty understanding this semester and held optional meetings each week where students could ask questions. The course was your best 10 out of 12 discussion posts and best 3 out of 4 exams. It was pretty easy to get an A in this course and Dr.  was always genuinely kind and caring to his students.

I had this professor for research methods and data analysis and enjoyed both of them! This is one of the best professors I have had at OSU. Professor  really cares about everyone and is ready to help if you have questions. The class is also really organized and super clear. Not too much homework and the tests were fair.
Wonderful prof. One of the best at Ohio State!

Amazing professor, challenging but wildly interesting & enjoyable course. Dr.  was very supportive, always accessible outside of class, seems genuinely invested in students' growth. I never felt overlooked even as an undergrad in a graduate course. One of my favorite classes/profs to date!

Dr Lount is a masterful professor. I thoroughly enjoyed his lectures, his teaching methodologies, and his efforts to help students even beyond what was required in the classroom. I would take him again for another subject in a heart-beat. His lectures were always interesting, and his in class negotiations gave a lot of practical experience.

Super nice professor who works to make sure that you learn what you'll use in your career. Is readily available to help students who need it and works to get to know students, which is uncommon at large universities like OSU.

Dr.  is an amazing professor!! I took another one of his course in AU 2021 and I absolutely loved it. Dr.  is amazing at lecturing and he has a way of making sure that you remember the material being taught. Although the exams can be challenging, he is always open to help during his office hours. Definitely recommend!!

The best class I've taken at Ohio State so far. Small class, about 15 people and totally focused on case studies. For older students, great way to apply what you've learned in other classes. For freshmen, great opportunity to learn from her and students that have been in the program

Dr.  was one of the most passionate educators I had the privilege of learning from during my 4 years at Ohio State. The course I took with him was just a GE and had nothing to do with my major, yet it was one of my favorite classes. He is a truly inspirational teacher and one of the best professors I have ever had.

Hands down THE best professor here at OSU Marion. Her class was the highlight of my semester, and as long as you do your work and study, you'll do amazing in this class. I have never met such a well-respected, kind, and charismatic professor before! I truly wish her all the best. Thank you for everything, Dr. !

Dr.  is one of the BEST professors and faculty at OSU! He is very professional, caring, and willing to help students pass his course(s). His teaching style and compassion for students makes attending OSU worthwhile. He certainly had a positive impact on my graduate school experience. I highly recommend him! Dr.  rocks!
